title: cornbread
directions: Over low heat, cook milk, cornmeal and salt until the mixture thickens. Stir in beaten egg yolk and cheese. Beat egg white until stiff and fold in. Place in muffin tins that have been sprayed with non-stick spray. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Saute celery and onion until soft over medium heat.
Add flour and make roux; cook for 3 minutes, then begin adding milk slowly and stir.
Add remaining ingredients and let soup simmer slowly. Add cooked and diced potatoes and serve.

title: crabmeat quiche
directions: Beat eggs.
Stir in half and half, onion, salt and pepper. Sprinkle crabmeat and cheese in pan.
Pour egg mixture over top. Sprinkle with parsley.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° for 30 minutes.

title: easy chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onion in small amount of oil.
When transparent, add cream cheese and cubed chicken.
Stir until cheese is softened and well mixed.
Put about 1/4 cup of chicken mixture on each tortilla and roll.
Place in a greased casserole dish.
Cover enchiladas with grated cheese.
Pour whipping cream (unwhipped) over enchiladas.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(To decrease fat use lite cream cheese and "Mission" tortillas.
These have only 1 gram of fat per serving.
When making for my diabetic daughter, I use milk instead of cream, but flavor is best when using cream.)

title: potatoes deluxe
directions: Put 1/2 cup melted oleo in baking dish.
Mix potatoes, onions, soup, sour cream and cheese; pour into baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Mix rest of oleo with cornflake crumbs; put on top of potatoes.
Bake 15 minutes more.
Serves 6.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: Place a layer of sliced potatoes in bottom of greased casserole dish; add a layer of sliced onion.
Then layer potatoes and onion again.
Combine cheese soup and milk and pour over previous layers.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put paprika on top and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Mix well and pat into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix well and pour in deep pie plate. Drain juice from one can peaches and add 3/4 cup sugar to peaches. Pour this over top of batter.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Heat until lukewarm the milk, margarine and molasses.
Pretest dry yeast as recommended on package and let rise.
Add lukewarm milk, margarine and molasses.
Add salt and flours.

title: popovers
directions: Break eggs into bowl.
Add milk, flour and salt.
Mix well with spoon.
Fill greased muffin pan 3/4 full.
Put in cold oven. Set control to 450°, then turn oven on.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Do not open oven door.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugars and shortening. Add eggs and beat.
Add vanilla, soda, cream of tartar and flour.
Mix well.
Roll into balls the size of a walnut.
Dip bottom of glass in sugar and press down. Bake at 350° for about 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs and milk.
Sift dry ingredients and add gradually to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla. Chill.
Roll thin.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Decorate as desired.
This recipe may be used in a cookie press, add 1/4 cup or more flour as needed.

title: ham and cheese omelet
directions: Spray pan with Pam.
Beat eggs, pepper, salt and water together.
Mix ham and cheese into mixture.
Pour into heated Pam pan.
When solid, flip over.
May add green peppers and onions.

title: homemade yogurt
directions: Scald
milk
(until
skins or 180°).
Let cool to 110°. Add gelatin
to
yogurt.
Stir
well.
After
milk cools, add yogurt to milk, stirring well.
Pour into 5 pint jars.
(Have jars warm.)
Let set on pilot light (complete bottom) of oven all night.
Take out in morning and put in refrigerator.
Let set until evening.
Yields 5 pints.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
In top of double boiler, beat egg yolks slightly.
Stir in milk, pumpkin, 1/2 cup sugar, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cook over hot water until thickened. Add softened gelatin and stir until thoroughly dissolved.
Cool about 1 hour in refrigerator.

title: old-fashioned noodles
directions: Combine flour, beaten egg, shortening, salt and water; mix until dough is soft.
Divide into three parts.
Roll out very thin; let dough dry for 20 minutes.
Cut in small strips; drop in broth.
Cook noodles until tender; stir.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Sprinkle 1/3 cup sugar over 2 cups sliced strawberries and let stand.
Prepare one package strawberry gelatin according to directions on package.
Chill until syrupy; beat with a rotary beater until fluffy, fold in strawberries and chill until firm.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour into pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or so.
Cool.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: In medium bowl, stir flour, baking powder, salt and sugar. In small bowl, beat egg and milk until blended.
Add to flour mixture with margarine.
Stir just until moistened.
Batter will be lumpy.
Fold in blueberries.
Turn into muffin tins.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: chocolate meringue pie
directions: Cook the pie crusts according to directions.
Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add the rest and double boil until very thick.
Pour mixture in pie crusts.
Add meringue on top and bake at 375° until brown.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix well.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Allow to cool.

title: creamy banana cheesecake
directions: Combine cream cheese, vanilla and sugar and mix well.
Stir in 1 cup whipped topping.
Place 1 cup sliced bananas at the bottom of the pie crust.
Spread cheese mixture over the bananas. Place remainder of bananas on top of the cream cheese mixture. Combine milk and pudding mix and stir until smooth.
Add 1 cup whipped topping and mix well.
Place this mixture over the bananas and chill for several hours before serving.

title: cranberry nut muffins
directions: In a bowl, beat the eggs. Add orange juice and oil.
Stir in dry ingredients just until moistened. Fold in cranberries and pecans.
Spoon into 12 greased or paper lined muffin cups (cups will be almost full).
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chocolate sauce cake
directions: Melt margarine, Crisco, cocoa and water in saucepan.
Mix in bowl the flour and sugar.
Add saucepan mixture.
Add eggs, mix well.
Add buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, bread crumbs, onion, milk, egg and next 4 ingredients; gently shape into 1-inch balls.

title: honey butter
directions: Cream the butter until light and fluffy.
Blend in honey. Keep refrigerated.
Serve on bread or muffins.
Yields 1 cup.

title: spritz
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add beaten egg yolks and flavoring. Add flour and mix well.
Press dough through cookie press, making S shapes and bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: craig claibornes pancake
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Melt	1/2
stick of butter or margarine
in
a large east-iron fry pan.
Mix flour, milk and nutmeg;
add
well beaten eggs. Pour into fry pan.	Bake about 15 minutes; sprinkle with 10x sugar. Serve hot.

title: mr. deli potato casserole
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Melt the butter and pour into the bottom of a 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Add 1/2 package of the hash browns.
In a separate bowl, combine the soup, sour cream, milk and onions.
Pour 1/2 of the mixture over the potatoes.
Spread 1 cup of the Cheddar cheese over that.
Layer the other 1/2 package of Doritos, then the rest of the soup mixture and 1 cup of Cheddar cheese again.
Cover with the crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: crispy eggplant
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
On wax paper, combine next 3 ingredients.
Brush both sides with mayonnaise mixture.
Coat with crumb mixture.
Place in pan or on cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 17 minutes.

title: apple cider pie
directions: Roll half of pastry to 1/8-inch thickness on a lightly floured surface.
Place in pie plate and set aside.
Combine cider and sugar in a large saucepan; bring to a boil.
Add apples; cook, uncovered, 8 minutes or until apples are tender.
Drain, reserving syrup.
Add enough water to syrup to measure 1 1/3 cups liquid; return syrup mixture and apples to saucepan.

title: seven layer jello
directions: Make orange, lime,
strawberry and lemon Jell-O according to package directions using 1 1/2 cups water each.

title: microwave macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni. Spray a 9 x 13 Pyrex oblong dish for baking. Add some macaroni. Add some of the cheese and stir into macaroni. Add other ingredients, except the rest of cheese and crushed crackers. Add rest of cheese and crushed crackers at the last. Place in microwave oven and cook for 3 minutes on High. Cook another 3 minutes or until cheese is good and melted.

title: hawaiian chicken salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and let set overnight.
Add remaining ingredients before serving.

title: seasoned potatoes
directions: Place sliced potatoes in a pan.
Place margarine in the pan. Sprinkle
seasoning
salt
over the potatoes.
Cover and bake at 350°for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cappuccino muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Combine coffee and milk, add eggs, butter and vanilla.
Stir into dry ingredients until just moistened.
Fold in chips.
Spray muffin tins with non-stick spray.
Fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 17 to 20 minutes.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes then remove to wire rack.
Serve with Cream Cheese Spread.

title: junior mints cheesecake
directions: Place Junior Mints in freezer and preheat oven to 350°.
With an electric mixer or food processor, combine cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Chop cold Junior Mints and sprinkle onto cheesecake.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until just set.
Cool on wire rack, then chill several hours or overnight.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cocoa fudge
directions: Place cocoa, sugar, cream of tartar and milk in saucepan; mix well.
Place over heat and cook, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Cover and cook 2 minutes longer.
Uncover and cook until mixture forms a soft ball when dropped from spoon into cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, but do not stir.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add vanilla and beat until creamy or until shine disappears.
Pour onto greased pan.
Cut when cool and serve.

title: raw veggie dip
directions: Mix well.
Let dip set for about an hour to let onion soften. Serve with raw carrots, red peppers, mushrooms, celery, pretzels, anything good for dipping.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream sugars, margarine and egg; add salt.
Stir in milk, baking soda, vanilla and flour.
Add rhubarb.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Sprinkle top with 1/4 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon and bake.

title: brown rice and lentil stew
directions: Combine all with 2 cups water and cook uncovered for 1 hour.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a greased casserole dish. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: easy chili dip
directions: In a pie plate, spread out cream cheese evenly.
Empty contents of chili onto the cream cheese (take out lumps of orange, they are fat calories no one needs), then sprinkle on shredded cheese.
Cook in a 350° oven for approximately 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: congealed cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add cranberry sauce and crushed pineapple.
Let chill until partially jelled.
Add sour cream and mix well.
Let congeal until firm.

title: cornstarch light batter
directions: In a bowl stir together first 5 ingredients.
Add water and egg; stir until smooth.
Pour 1 quart corn oil into a large skillet until hot.
Dip vegetables or chicken.
Fry 2 to 3 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Saute mushrooms and chopped onion in butter.
Melt cheese and mushroom soup; add to mixture.
Add Tabasco sauce, soy sauce and salt and pepper to taste.
Place in layers in a large casserole dish with half the sauce, beans and water chestnuts.
Place onion rings on top and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: salmon ball(appetizer)
directions: Debone and drain salmon.
Combine ingredients.
Shape into ball.
Roll in 1/3 cup finely chopped pecans or walnuts.
Makes 1 (5-inch) salmon ball.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and put in buttered 9 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle cherries over batter.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar over cherries.
Pour boiling water over all.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pumpkin soup
directions: In a soup pot, melt the butter over medium heat on top of the stove.
Saute the onion in it for 5 minutes.
Add the stock, ginger, nutmeg and pumpkin.
Bring the mixture to a boil.
Turn the heat down to low and simmer the soup for 10 minutes, until it is thick.
Stir it every so often so that it doesn't stick to the pan and burn.
Serve in a Pumpkin Tureen.

title: reese's peanut butter cup cookies
directions: Cream margarine, peanut butter and sugars.
Beat in egg and vanilla and mix well.
Sift dry ingredients and blend in.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Using miniature muffin tins, place small amount of dough in each muffin cup.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from oven immediately and press candy cup in each until top only of peanut cup shows.
Let sit a bit before removing from tins.

title: easy ice cream
directions: Dissolve
ice cream powder in a little milk.
Add Eagle Brand milk.
Mix and put in freezer.
Add any fruit or whatever flavoring, such as peaches, strawberries, bananas, pineapple, fruit
cocktail, vanilla, etc.
Then finish filling with sweet milk and freeze.

title: crock pot pepper steak
directions: Brown round steak strips. Combine browned steak with soy sauce, onion, garlic, sugar, salt, pepper and ginger in a crock pot. Cover and cook on low 5 to 6 hours or until meat is tender. Add tomatoes and peppers. Cook on low 1 hour longer. Mix corn starch and water until blended. Add to crock pot. Cook on high until thickened. Serve over noodles or rice.

title: coconut cream candy
directions: Melt butter in pan; set aside.
Put sugar and milk in pan; heat slowly stirring until sugar dissolves and mixture boils. Boil 12 to 15 minutes; remove from heat.
Add coconut and vanilla. Beat until creamy.
Pour into buttered pan; let cool.
Cut in pieces.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake yellow cake per box instructions in a 9 x 13-inch pan. While cake is still warm, beat crushed pineapple, juice and all. Pour over the cake.
While cake and pineapple cool, mix the instant vanilla pudding per box instructions.
Spread over the cooled cake. When the pudding is set, spread defrosted Cool Whip over the entire cake, then sprinkle the coconut all over and finish off with nut topping.

title: frozen mud pie sandwiches
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a small heavy saucepan. Bring the mixture to a boil over medium heat, stirring frequently with a whisk. Turn down to a simmer and cook on low heat for about 2 minutes or until thick. Stir
the mixture frequently while it cooks. When finished, remove the mixture from the heat and stir in the margarine and vanilla. Cover and chill thoroughly.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix powdered sugar, milk and vanilla pudding until thick and smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan; lay graham crackers, covering the bottom of pan.
Spread 1/2 of pudding mix on crackers.
Top with another layer of crackers on pudding. Spread remaining pudding on crackers.
Lay crackers on pudding and spread icing on crackers.
Sprinkle with pecans (optional). Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.
Keep refrigerated.

title: magic biscuits
directions: Combine flour, soda, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Cut Crisco into flour mix with pastry blender.
Dissolve yeast in 4 tablespoons warm water.
Add to dry mixture and add buttermilk. Roll out; cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on cookie sheets.
Allow to rest 10 minutes. Freeze. Place in Ziploc bags.
Use as needed. Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix well and chill.
May add chopped pecans if desired.

title: mystery cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and margarine until crumbly.
Put 1/2 of mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Peel zucchini and slice to look like apples (enough to make 8 cups). Put in saucepan and cook with 2/3 cup lemon juice.
Add 1 cup sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add 1/2 to 2/3 cup of the crust mixture.
Cook a few more minutes until zucchini are tender.
Pour on top of baked crust.
Add 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon to remainder of crust mixture and put on top of zucchini.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and butter.
Add eggs and pecans.
Pour into tart shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken soup
directions: Cook chicken breast and onion together.
(Don't overcook.) Debone chicken.
Cut in bite-size pieces.
In a large soup pot, put in chicken, cream of chicken soup and chicken broth from cooked chicken.
Add chicken bouillon and noodles.
Grate off carrot finely into soup mixture.
Add broccoli.
Sprinkle with garlic and pepper.
Stir until mixed to desired consistency.
Add more broth, if needed.
Don't overcook.
Cook until noodles are done.

title: chocolate cornmeal cookies
directions: Mix butter or margarine and sugar in a large bowl.
Add egg and beat well.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Drop dough from a teaspoon on a greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: green beans deluxe
directions: Cut beans crosswise in 1-inch pieces.
Heat beans, water and salt to boiling point in a 2-quart saucepan.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Add celery.
Cover and cook until beans are tender, about 10 minutes; drain.
Heat butter, lemon juice, seasoned salt, olives and pimento on low heat until butter melts.
Toss with beans.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Put margarine and sugar in pan.
Melt.
Pour over pretzels. Put in pan and bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Let cool.

title: pig cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, oranges and eggs.
Pour into 3 layer pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chewy caramel bars
directions: Melt caramels with evaporated milk in double boiler or microwave.
Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Reserve 1 cup.
Press remaining crumb mixture into bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over baked crust. Spread caramel mixture evenly over chocolate chips.
Sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture.
Continue baking for 20 minutes.
Chill 2 hours.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk, refrigerate until thick.
Mix in sour cream and cool whip.
Layer vanilla wafers, bananas, and pudding mixture in large casserole dish.
Enjoy!

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and oil; add bananas and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add to mixture.
Fold in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients down to mayonnaise.
Hold the tomato slices and potato chips.
Add just enough mayonnaise to moisten. Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and top with tomatoes.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Top with potato chips and extra cheese if desired.
Bake a few more minutes.

title: chicken with mushrooms and spinach
directions: Cook chicken.
Remove; keep warm.
In same skillet, cook spinach and mushrooms; stir for 3 minutes.
Stir in Lipton mix that has been blended with water.
Bring to a boil until sauce thickens. Pour vegetable mixture over chicken.
Serves 4.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Preheat broiler, placing chicken on broiler-pan rack.
Rub chicken with oil, sprinkle with cumin.
Broil chicken 6 inches from heat for 8 minutes, or until no longer pink in center. Remove into foil to keep warm.

title: nondairy ice cream
directions: Mix sugar, coffee creamer and flour.
Add beaten eggs and one quart water.
Bring to a boil, stirring continually.
Remove from heat and cool.
Pour into container and add whipped topping, cold water and vanilla.
Freeze according to freezer directions.

title: steak parmesan
directions: Beat together the egg, water and pepper.
Combine crumbs and half of the cheese.
Dip steaks into egg mixture, then into the crumbs.
In skillet, brown steaks in hot oil.
Drain on paper towel.
Arrange steaks in a baking dish.
Top with cooked eggplant slice, if desired.
Cover with pizza sauce and remaining cheese. Bake for 20 minutes at 325°.
Serves 4.

title: italian style tomato sauce
directions: Blanch tomatoes (30 seconds for Roma; 1 minute for regular). Remove from heat and let cool.
Now peel.
Cut tomatoes in half and remove the seeds.
Strain the excess water.
Now puree.

title: easy girl scout surprise
directions: Crush the Girl Scout cookies and line the bottom of a small glass Pyrex dish. Save 1/2 cup for top.
Mix vanilla pudding according to directions, then mix with softened cream cheese.
Set aside.
Mix chocolate pudding according to directions and mix with Cool Whip. Set aside.
Spread vanilla pudding mixture on top of cookies in the pan.
Spread the chocolate pudding mixture on top of the vanilla mixture. Top with Cool Whip and the remaining cookies.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugars together until it is creamy.
Add the egg, stirring it in.
Sift your flour, soda and salt together, then add your peanut butter now or you could add the peanut butter before you add your flour and other ingredients.
Put in your vanilla and water, stirring it all until all is mixed.
Bake at 350°.

title: star chicken(serves 4)
directions: Saute garlic and onion in olive oil until golden.
Add cubed chicken.
Aside, mix cool bouillon, water, cornstarch and wine and add to chicken mixture.
Cook, uncovered, on low heat at first, and then for 3 minutes on medium heat.
Serve over rice or angel hair pasta.
(Green beans may be added as last step while on medium heat; optional.)

title: dessert pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees. Press cookie dough into 12 inch pizza pan. Beat cream cheese, milk and sugar with wire whisk. Stir in whipped topping. Spread on cookie crust. Garnish with toppings.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Butter an 8 x 8 x 2 inch pan. In a 3 1/2 quart saucepan, mix sugar with dry gelatin. Add milk, corn syrup, chocolate and butter. Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, to 238 F. on candy

thermometer, or until a little in cold water forms a soft ball. Remove from heat; pour into mixing bowl. Stir in vanilla. Cool for 30 minutes. Beat with wooden spoon until thickens. Stir in walnuts. Spread into prepared pan. Let cool, then cut into squares. Makes 2 1/2 pounds.

title: chicken curry
directions: Place chicken in oil and place onion and pepper on top.
Cook 10 minutes, then add sauce.

title: orange breakfast drink
directions: Place all ingredients into a blender and blend until frothy (foamy).
Serve immediately.

title: crazy chocolate cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add wet ingredients (oil, vinegar and vanilla).
Gently pour water over entire ingredients.
Mix with fork until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.
Frosting is optional; makes an interesting crunchy top on its own.

title: peg's beef stroganoff
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add beef and set aside.
Add butter to skillet.
Add mushrooms and cook 5 minutes.
Add sherry and boil 2 minutes.
Add beef broth and cornstarch.
Stir in sour cream.
Add beef and heat 1 to 2 more minutes.
Do not boil.
Serve over noodles.

title: peanut butter dressing(sauce)
directions: In small bowl, stir together peanut butter and corn syrup until blended. Stir in milk. Cover and refrigerate. Serve over fresh fruit. Makes about 1 1/3 cups.

title: lemon coconut cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 round pans (8 or 9-inch).
Prepare cake mix as directed on package, except add lemon peel with the water.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Cool completely.
Prepare lemon filling.
Put filling between layers.

title: mu shu pork
directions: Makes filling for (8) 6 inch chinese pancakes.
Presoak mushrooms and lily buds in hot water for 15 minutes and drain. Pour 2 Tbsp. oil in a hot wok and add pork, stir fry for 3 minutes. Push up sides of wok and add garlic, onion and soy sauce.
Stir fry 30 seconds.
Push up sides of wok add remaining oil, bok choy, lillies and cloud ear mushrooms, stir fry for 1 minute.
Remove all ingredients and reserve.
Add eggs and scramble in wok.
Before eggs set add broth, salt , pepper, sugar and reserved ingredients. Stir until combined.
Serve with the pancakes and/or plum or Hoison sauce.
All are available in better supermarkets or asian specialty shops.

title: meringue kisses
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy; add salt and cream of tartar. Continue beating until stiff; gradually beat in sugar.
Add vanilla last, then add what you like (chocolate chips, coconut, Rice Krispies, nuts).
Drop by spoonful on brown paper.
Bake for about 40 minutes at 275°.
Remove from paper while still warm. If difficult to remove, set paper on damp towel.

title: cheese grits
directions: Add butter and cheese to grits; mix until well blended.
Add eggs and milk.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: belva's fruit dip
directions: Mix together and serve as a dip for fruits.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Cut bacon in small pieces.
Saute bacon and green pepper and onion.
Drain.
Mix with all other ingredients, pour into baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple tapioca
directions: Soak tapioca in grapefruit juice for 5 minutes.
Add all other ingredients, slowly bring to a boil and allow to boil for 1 minute. Place in four individual serving bowls and chill thoroughly before serving.
Serves 4.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix dough.
Chill in refrigerator.
Roll into balls the size of walnut.
Roll in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: easy casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line the sides of 10 x 10 x 1-inch buttered casserole with hash.
Put vegetables in center and top with Tater Tots and onion rings.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Grind the vegetables and sprinkle with salt and let stand overnight.
Rinse and drain all of the water out of the vegetables.
Combine the mustard and celery seed, vinegar and turmeric and pour over vegetables.
Heat to boiling and simmer for 3 minutes.
Add the cornstarch and water and stir until thickened. Seal in sterilized jars.

title: mother's old fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: In large bowl, blend margarine, sugars, eggs and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Combine flour, salt, baking soda, cinnamon, cloves and allspice.
Add to creamed mixture; mix to blend.
Stir in oats and pecans. Drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet lined with parchment paper.
Flatten with floured fork to 2-inch diameter (will spread to 4-inch when baked).
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheet; remove to cooling rack.
Sift confectioners sugar over tops.
Yields 3 dozen large cookies.

title: cheese sausage bake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cubed bread, cheese and sausage.
Mix eggs, 2 1/2 cups milk and mustard.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
When ready to bake, mix mushroom soup with rest of milk and pour over top.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until brown.

title: green bean bundles
directions: Cut several pieces of bacon in half.
Wrap each half slice of bacon around 8 to 10 whole green beans and secure with a toothpick.
Make a glaze from the melted butter, brown sugar, salt and pepper.
Place the Green Bean Bundles into a baking dish. Place the bundles close together because the bacon will shrink during cooking.
Cover the bean bundles with the glaze and bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Uncover the last few minutes in order for the bacon to brown.

title: butterscotch candy
directions: Combine sugars, milk and butter in heavy saucepan; cook until soft ball stage, 235° on a candy thermometer.
Add remaining ingredients.
Remove from heat; beat until mixture begins to thicken, about 1 minute.
Pour into buttered 8-inch square pan; cool.
Cut into serving pieces.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer
ingredients:
crushed pineapple, Comstock apples and sprinkle or
sift box of dry cake mix.
Melt margarine and drizzle across top.
Sprinkle
pecans
on top.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: no cook cookies
directions: Roll out bread dough from favorite bread recipe until 1/4 inch thick.
Cut into shapes with cookie cutters.
Place on oiled sheet to rise.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: quick macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni as directed.
Meanwhile, grate cheese.
Combine dry ingredients with 1/4 cup milk.
After pasta is drained, return macaroni to pot (do not rinse).
Add 2 pats of butter and remaining ingredients.
Stir.
Allow a few minutes to melt, then stir again and serve.

title: crunchy chicken cheese cake
directions: Use 3-quart oblong baking dish.
Place chicken; top with cheese.
Stir soup and spread over cheese.
Top with tomatoes, combined margarine and stuffing.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water until it spins a fine hair.
Pour in peanuts.
Cook until light brown.
Remove from heat.
Add soda, salt, butter and vanilla.
Pour on a well-greased cookie sheet.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in airtight jar.

title: wienie bake
directions: Cook and mash potatoes with margarine and milk.
Heat oven to 450°.
Slice wieners lengthwise 2/3 of the way through and place in baking dish. Spoon hot potatoes into opening of wieners, using any leftover potatoes around and between wieners.
Cover top of mixture with cheese slices and bake until wieners are hot and cheese is melted and slightly brown.

title: layered summer salad
directions: Put lettuce in large bowl.
Sprinkle with celery, water chestnuts and green onions.
In small bowl, mix mayonnaise and seasoned salt.
Spread 3/4 cup mayonnaise over celery, water chestnuts and onions.
Sprinkle with peas and cheese.
Spread remaining 3/4 cup mayonnaise over peas and cheese.
Garnish with chopped eggs, tomatoes and bacon.
Refrigerate 2 hours or overnight.
Store in refrigerator.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: heart healthy lasagne
directions: Saute onions and garlic in oil until soft.
Crumble ground beef and cook.
Drain.
Add tomatoes, paste, oregano and pepper; simmer for 30 minutes.
Combine cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, 1 1/2 cups Mozzarella cheese and parsley; set aside.

title: beef supreme
directions: Brown ground beef and drain grease.
Add sugar, garlic salt, tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Cook noodles according to package. Drain off water.
Mix in sour cream, cream cheese and green onions.
Place half noodle mixture in casserole dish.
Put in a layer of meat mixture.
Repeat layers.
Top with grated cheese. Cook in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: mystery pie
directions: In one bowl, whip the Dream Whip according to directions.
In another bowl, beat milk and lemon juice. Mix both together, adding nuts.
Pour into baked pie crust and chill in refrigerator.
Makes 2 pies.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and milk.
Put in baking dish and cook in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Mix cheese with milk and pour over; brown.

title: scalloped carrots
directions: Peel and slice carrots.
Cook with small amount of sugar, about 1 tablespoon for 15 minutes.
Drain in saucepan.
Grate onion in butter or oil and cook about 1 minute.

title: seven minute strawberry preserves
directions: Place berries in saucepan.
Sift the 1/2 cup sugar over berries.
Add lemon juice.
Let set overnight.
Next morning, add 2 1/2 cups sugar.
Heat to boiling and boil 7 minutes.
Pour in jars and seal.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, spices and salt together.
Add eggs, oil and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add apples and nuts.
Stir until mixed.
Pour into greased, floured tube pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° until done.
Place in heavy brown paper bag immediately.
Close tightly.
Let stay 1 hour.

title: honey chicken
directions: Line broiler pan with foil.
Place chicken on foil, skin side up, and pour the sauce over.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Baste every 20 minutes.

title: sand cups
directions: Decorations:
You can use miniature umbrellas, gummy sharks, candy stars or chopped peanuts for decoration.

title: make ahead coleslaw
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in large bowl, mix well and set aside.

title: seafood batter
directions: Mix buttermilk and baking powder in bowl.
Mix meal, flour and salt.
Coat fish twice.
Place on tray and refrigerate 2 hours before frying.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, Crisco and salt (with fork).
Add water.
Mix; roll in ball and roll out on floured board or smooth tea towel.

title: yam biscuits
directions: Scrub the yams in cold water; do not pare.
Cover them with boiling water and boil in a covered saucepan just until tender when pierced with a fork.
Drain; remove skins and mash; measure enough to make 2 cups.
Reserve any remaining for some other use.
With a spoon, beat the shortening into the 2 cups mashed hot yams until blended; cool.
In a medium size bowl, stir together the flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add the yam mixture and work together until blended.
If dough is very sticky, add flour sparingly.
On a pastry cloth with a stockinet-covered rolling pin, roll out 1/2-inch thick.
With a floured round 2-inch cutter, cut out biscuits.
Place slightly apart on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in preheated 450° oven until browned 15 to 18 minutes. (Bottoms of the biscuits will be very dark, but they will not taste scorched.)
Rush to the table while they are still puffy and hot. They will sink slightly as they cool.
"They are crusty outside and soft inside.
Serve them with plenty of butter."
Makes almost 2 dozen.

title: chicken & dressing casserole
directions: Cook and Debone chicken, beat eggs in a very large bowl. Add soups, pepper, broth, chicken,
onion, cheese and stuffing. Bake in 9 X 13 pan at 350 degrees for 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Cook chicken breasts.
Cut into strips and cook in 3/4 cup Miracle Whip in a large skillet on medium-high for 3 minutes.
Add frozen vegetables.
Stir in 2 tablespoons soy sauce and garlic powder.
Continue cooking 5 minutes until chicken is cooked through.
Serve over rice.
Yields 4 servings.

title: minorcan sausage pilau
directions: Saute onions and peppers in small
amount
of
oil; add tomato paste or sauce and hot pepper.
Cook
down.
Add water; cook down again.
Do this several times.

title: zesty bacon dip
directions: In blender, place cottage cheese and cream cheese; blend until smooth.
Stir in bacon, scallions, parsley, horseradish and diced pimientos.
Chill for 1 hour.
Serve with Twigs snack sticks.

title: peanut butterscotch bites
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, combine butterscotch morsels and peanut butter.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until smooth.
Remove from heat and stir in Rice Krispies, mixing until well coated.
Spray a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan with vegetable spray. Press mixture into pan evenly.
Chill until firm.
Cut into small bars to serve.
Store in an airtight container in refrigerator.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Mix and put into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: 3-in-one cheese ball
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, Cheddar cheese, milk, onion and Worcestershire sauce until mix is fluffy.
If a smoother spread is needed, process in a food processor until creamy.
Divide into thirds (about 1 cup each).
Shape first portion into a ball, roll in cracked pepper.
Add Blue cheese to the second ball.
Add garlic powder to the third.
Mix well.
Shape into one ball.
Roll in bacon bits.
Cover and refrigerate.
Let stand at room temperature, then serve with crackers.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix the soups and the chicken broth.
Layer rice, chopped broccoli and part of the soup.
Add chicken.
Pour remaining soup over chicken.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and cheese of your choice.
Bake in a 350° oven until cheese melts and crumbs start to brown a little bit.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spread on tray or platter.
Top with shredded cheese, lettuce, black olives, tomatoes and onion if desired.
Serve with Tostitos.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Let ice cream soften. Crush cookies and mix everything together.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.

title: smoked trout and dill spread(great for the holidays)
directions: Line a 2 1/2 cup bowl or mold with plastic. Coarsely chop 2 eggs. Place in large bowl. Add next 7 ingredients, mix thoroughly. Season with salt and pepper.

title: onion pie
directions: Melt butter in skillet, add onions, cover and simmer over low heat for 10 minutes or until onions are transparent.
Beat egg yolks with salt until yolks are light and thick.
Stir in cream. Add onions and flour; stir enough to blend.
Whip egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Fold gently into onion mixture.
Pour into baked and cooled pie shell.
Sprinkle with bacon.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown and custard is firm.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix together
the
flour
and sugar. Cut in the Crisco. Add the
buttermilk and soda mixture to the yeast mixture.
Do not let rise.
Roll out on pastry sheet and cut biscuits. Bake at 450° until brown.
Or these may be stored in greased, large mixing bowl in
refrigerator
and
baked as needed.
Makes 25 biscuits.

title: winners circle pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour; add eggs and then butter.
Add English walnuts, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake 30 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.
You may have to bake it longer because ovens vary.
Test with a toothpick.
It should be chewy but not runny and is traditionally served warm.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Drain off grease.
Add tomato soup or sauce and 1 cup water.
Add all other ingredients and simmer over low heat for 30 minutes.
While sauce is simmering, prepare spaghetti.
When done, serve over spaghetti.

title: holiday tea
directions: Combine ingredients.
Use 1 teaspoon per cup of hot boiling water.
Stir and serve hot.

title: creamy clam chowder
directions: Combine 1st 5 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer until potatoes are tender.
Add rest of ingredients, stirring constantly until thick and bubbly.
Yields 5 cups, 176 calories and 2.4 g fat per 1 cup serving.

title: texas aggie brownies
directions: Mix well with mixer.
Pour over first layer.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook frozen broccoli as directed on package; drain.
Place broccoli in 9 x 13 Pyrex dish.
Cube Velveeta cheese and 1/2 stick of butter; put on top of broccoli.
Crumble Ritz crackers over mixture.
Melt 1/2 stick of butter; pour over crackers.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter gems
directions: Mix together margarine, peanut butter and powder sugar
in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips; spread over top.
Chill.
Cut in small squares when slightly chilled.

title: bakers frosting
directions: Put all ingredients in mixing bowl and mix with an electric mixer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Works great even for decorating.

title: orange haystacks
directions: In a large saucepan, over very low heat, melt chips with oil, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients until noodles are well coated.
Remove from heat. Drop by tablespoons onto plastic wrap or wax paper.

title: stuffed shrimp
directions: *Mix crackers and cheese about half and half.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown lightly bacon, ground beef and chopped onion.
Mix together salt, dry mustard, vinegar, catsup and brown sugar. Combine mixtures and add beans.
Mix together and bake in covered dish at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry-pineapple jam
directions: Bring strawberries, sugar, pineapple and lemon juice to a full rolling boil. Add Certo and boil for additional 15 minutes. Skim off foam and spoon into jars. Heat lids in hot water and put on jars with bands. Make sure jars seal. Use large stockpot to cook in. Makes approximately 12 pints.

title: spanikopita
directions: Wash spinach well; discard stems.
Tear leaves into small pieces.
Pat dry.
Beat eggs, crumble cheese and mix together. Add to spinach.
Saute chopped onion in olive oil until browned. Add to spinach.
Season with salt, pepper and oregano to taste.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs and bananas.
Add the other ingredients. Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool and wrap in foil or Saran Wrap.

title: cheese-potato casserole
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and pour in greased casserole dish and top with crushed corn flakes and melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: butterscotch crumblies
directions: Melt butterscotch candy in double boiler.
Remove from heat and stir in noodles and peanuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: white chili
directions: Cook beans in chicken broth.
Saute onions in 1 Tbsp. butter, add chilies and spices.
Add other ingredients and cook 1 hour on low.
Garnish with sour cream, shredded cheese and green onions. Yield:
8 servings.

title: crunchy nut lentil roast
directions: Mix lentils and rice.
Add all other ingredients.
Put in a baking dish and sprinkle top with grated cheese.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Melt oleo.
Add flour and stir until blended.
Add onion, bell pepper and garlic.
Saute until tender.
Add fat from crawfish and cook about 10 minutes.
Add crawfish tails.
Cook another 15 minutes.
Season.
Just before serving, squeeze a little lemon juice over crawfish.
Serve over rice.
Flavor is improved if made the day before serving.

title: pig skins
directions: Cut hot dogs into fourth pieces.
Cut bacon slices into thirds pieces.
wrap each hotdog piece with a piece of bacon and secure it with a toothpick.
Place all wrapped hotdogs in a crockpot. If you run out of bacon just throw the extra hot dogs in there too!
Then pour one box of light brown sugar on top.
Stir occasionally.
They are ready to eat when the brown sugar has melted completely.

title: lime punch
directions: Combine ingredients and add water to taste.

title: impossible quiche *
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 10-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion evenly over bottom of pie pan.
Place remaining ingredients in blender on high speed for 1 minute.
Pour in pie pan.
Bake until golden (about 50 minutes).
Let stand 5 minutes.
Leftovers can be refrigerated.

title: party cake
directions: Drain oranges.
Mix all cake ingredients together.
Cook cake until done and then let cool.

title: morrocan pizzas
directions: Put in blender and mix.
Spread on English muffins.
Cut in quarters.
Bake at 350° for fifteen minutes.
Can put in freezer. Ready to bake.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, water and flour until thick.
Then add box of strawberry Jell-O while the mixture is still hot.
Stir until well mixed.
Put strawberries into the mixture.
Pour into pie shells (ready baked).
Makes 2 pies.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: pink party punch
directions: Prepare powdered drink mix according to package directions, chill.
Place ice cream and strawberries in punch bowl.
Pour in prepared drink.
Stir.
Serves 40.

title: caramel popcornnederland, texas
directions: Boil for 5 minutes and then add 1 tsp. baking soda.

title: better than butter (in every way)
directions: Clean pancake griddle by rubbing with salt, scraping it off with waxed paper.
Then rub a cloth saturated with cooking oil lightly over griddle, cakes won't stick.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put sugar in heavy skillet and melt sugar.
Measure peanuts, soda, salt and butter and put in one bowl.
After sugar melts, put in rest of ingredients all at once.
Stir rapidly and pour on well buttered pan.
Let cool and break.

title: oreo cake
directions: Crush cookies after removing the cream.
Combine cookies with melted butter.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Reserve 1/2 cup for top.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Mix cream cheese with sugar.
Add 1 container Cool Whip; spread over cookie layer.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Make chocolate pudding; spread over cream cheese layer. Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Spread second container of Cool Whip on top of the pudding.
Sprinkle with cookie crumbs.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix gently until just blended.
Put in greased bread tin. Bake at 375° in a metal pan.
Bake at 350° if using glass pan. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: texas um um's
directions: Mix together.
Press on bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Take out and let cool.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Prepare broccoli in bite-size pieces, slicing stems thin.
Add onions and raisins.
Heat vinegar.
Dissolve sugar; add mayonnaise and beat until smooth.
Pour over vegetables and refrigerate for several hours.
Sprinkle bacon in and stir just before serving.

title: old fashioned vanilla ice cream
directions: Separate the eggs and mix the milk, egg yolks, and sugar over low heat on the stove until sugar has dissolved.
Beat the egg whites until stiff and pour over the warm mixture and mix well. Add the vanilla and salt.
Place in the refrigerator for 30 minutes or until cold.
While this is cooling, whip the whipping cream.
Take mixture out of refrigerator and add the whipped cream.
Freeze according to your ice cream mixer directions.

title: date-nut chewies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 2 cookie sheets.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix flour, 1/2 cup of powdered sugar and butter.
Press out in a pizza pan and bake for 10 minutes at 400°.
Let cool.
Blend in a mixer 1 cup of powdered sugar, Cool Whip and cream cheese and spread on crust.
Top with sweetened strawberries or other fruit.

title: new orleans sugary treat
directions: Beat egg white with small amount of water until it forms a cream.
With your fingers work in the sugar until it forms a smooth paste.
Roll a small piece of this. Place between two pecan halves, then lightly roll in the paste, flattening the pecan somewhat.
The coating outside must be very, very light so that the delicate brown of the pecan meat shows through.
Set the pecans to dry.
Once dry they are ready to be served.

title: chicken kathleen
directions: Lightly sprinkle
chicken
with
salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Wrap each
breast
with several slices of bacon; place each breast on piece of dried beef in baking dish; add 3 pieces of beef between or around chicken.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Bake
at
for one hour or until done. Baste while cooking.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco very good.
Then add sugar and cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
Alternate flour mixture and milk.
Add vanilla and almond.

title: sausage cheese dip
directions: Heat until cheese is melted.
May be made and served in an electric skillet or kept on a heating tray while serving.
Serve with corn chips or tortilla chips.

title: strawberries chantilly
directions: Cut cleaned berries in half and cover with powdered sugar (1/2 cup) and rum.
Chill 30 minutes.
Whisk egg whites until stiff, adding 4 tablespoons powdered sugar.
Fold in chilled berries. Serve in sherbet glasses.
Top with whipped cream.

title: pecan finger cookies(diabetic)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a medium bowl stir all ingredients. With a fork, beat in 2 tablespoons very hot water until dough pulls away from sides and forms a ball.
Shape dough into 25 balls.
Place on a cookie sheet, 1 inch apart.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: apple relish
directions: Prepare and chop in small cubes, add 2 cups brown sugar and mix together. Cover with vinegar in cooking kettle, or heavy, large sauce pan, boil 20 minutes. Pack in sterilized jars and seal.

title: sausage bites
directions: In large skillet, brown sausage in butter; drain and set aside. In small bowl, stir together cornstarch, pineapple juice, cream of coconut, mustard and garlic powder. Add to sausage in skillet. Cook and stir until sauce thickens. Add pineapple, pepper and water chestnuts; heat through and serve. Refrigerate leftovers. Makes 40 appetizers.

title: beef pasty pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, combine beef, potatoes, carrots, celery, onion, soup, salt, poultry seasoning and pepper.
Mix well. Set aside.

title: clam chowder from the old pine tree inn
directions: Steam clams and reserve liquid.
Chop clams and set aside. In a large pot, saute onion in oil until clear, not brown.
Add celery, potatoes, water, reserved clam juice and clams; simmer until celery and potatoes are done.
Add remaining ingredients. Yield: 3 quarts.

title: tangy barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in small saucepan.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat and simmer until onion is well done.
Use to coat chicken, spareribs or other meats to broil or grill.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: 1. Heat oil and margarine.
2. Add minced garlic, shrimp, and cook till pink.
3. Add lemon juice, salt, pepper, and parsley.

title: enchiladas
directions: Cook onions, hamburger meat and bell pepper together until done.
Add chopped Velveeta cheese and ripe olives.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Mix enchilada sauce mix with tomato soup, tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Dilute with water if too thick.
Set aside.
Fill flour tortillas with meat and cheese mixture.
Roll up and place them seam side down in
a large greased pan.
Pour sauce over top of enchiladas.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top. Bake in oven at 400° until cheese is bubbly and slightly brown.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Brown muffin mix with onions.
Add chicken stock, salt, pepper and eggs.
Pour in baking dish.
Bake until brown at 400°.

title: mexican chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Use an 8 x 8 pan. Spray with vegetable/garlic oil. Put crushed chips in bottom of pan. Divide the 8 biscuits into 16. Place 8 of the halves on top of the chips. Brown onion, bell pepper and jalapeno in olive oil until tender in a skillet. Heat soup, Ro-Tel tomatoes and cheese until melted. Do not burn. Add the cooked chicken. Pour 1/2 of the chicken mixture on top of the biscuits, then add the remaining biscuits and cover with soup mixture. Cook for 30 minutes. Spread shredded cheese on top and put back in oven. Broil until brown.

title: no cook cookies
directions: In a large saucepan, mix margarine, sugar, milk and cocoa. Stir often and bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well and add oatmeal.
Mix well and drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper to cool.

title: ham and scalloped potatoes
directions: Heat 3 tablespoons margarine in 1 1/2-quart saucepan over low heat until melted.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and bubbly; remove from heat.
Stir in milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in parsley.

title: chicken and noodles supreme
directions: Cook chicken, reserving broth for cooking noodles. Add enough water to broth from chicken to cook noodles, leaving very little extra liquid. When noodles are tender, remove from heat and add cheese, stirring to melt it. Add chicken (which has been diced), celery soup and onion. Add enough evaporated milk to make it as juicy as you prefer. Salt and pepper, if desired. Place in large casserole. Sprinkle with paprika. Heat in moderate oven until bubbly and heated through.

title: strawberry icebox cake
directions: Pour water over gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Add frozen berries and stir until thawed.
Place cubed angel food cake in a 9 x 13 inch pan and pour jello mixture on top of cake.
Frost with whipped topping and refrigerate.

title: tomato pudding
directions: Melt margarine and pour over cubed bread in a greased 1-quart casserole dish.
Cook tomato sauce, brown sugar and salt for 5 minutes.
Pour over bread.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole(great for a crowd)
directions: *Asparagus may also be used.

title: macaroni and hamburger dinner
directions: Cook macaroni; drain water off.
Brown hamburger with chopped onion, chili powder and garlic powder.
Drain grease off.
Add ketchup and tomato sauce along with macaroni.
You could add grated cheese before serving.

title: jeff's corn and seafood soup
directions: Saute onions and shallots in cooking oil. Add bell peppers, tomato sauce, diced tomatoes, corn and soups. Cook until desired consistency. Add shrimp, crawfish, fish, sausage, scallops, okra, potatoes and rice. Add seasonings (salt, pepper and Cajun seasoning salt to taste). Cook 15 minutes or until seafood and sausage are done.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt and cinnamon; add flour mixture with the 2 cups sugar and oil.
Beat eggs and add with the mixture;
add
carrots
and blend.	Bake at 350° in layers for 30 minutes.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: easy and delicious lo-cal noodle pudding
directions: Boil noodles as directed.
Drain in colander.
Return them to warm pot and mix with margarine.
Mix all in pot or switch to a large bowl.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, eggs and apricot syrup in bowl.
Then mix with noodles.

title: kodiak king crab casserole
directions: Grease a 16-inch baking pan.
Put in half of the bread cubes. Mix crabmeat, mayonnaise, onion, pepper and celery.
Put on bread. Top with remaining bread squares.

title: pea soup
directions: Soak whole peas overnight; drain in morning.
Simmer all ingredients together for 2 to 3 hours in a covered pan.
Stir occasionally.

title: pork chop meal
directions: Brown chops; season with salt and pepper.
Wash rice and combine it with curry powder, soup and vegetables in 2-quart casserole.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well. Make paste of cocoa and coloring.
Add to mixture.

title: franklin nut cake
directions: Reserve 1 cup of flour to roll nuts and fruit in before adding to other ingredients.
Mix well the first 4 ingredients.
Add fruit and nut mixture, mixing well.
Bake in a 250° oven for
3 hours in tube pan.

title: chicken crunch
directions: In a shallow dish, combine 1/3 cup soup and 1/4 cup milk; set aside.
On waxed paper, lightly coat chicken with flour and dip into soup mixture.
On another piece of waxed paper, coat chicken with stuffing.

title: friendship cake
directions: Bake the fudge cake mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan according to package directions.
Cool completely.
Crumble cake into bottom of a large glass bowl such as a deep salad bowl.
Pour coffee over top of cake, if desired.
Mix 1 small chocolate instant pudding mix with cold milk.
Layer on top of cake.
Add layer of crushed Heath bars, saving some for a garnish on top.
Add large Cool Whip and sprinkle with remaining crushed Heath bar pieces.
Chill.

title: my mother's pound cake
directions: Have butter at room temperature.
Blend sugar, butter and 1 egg at a time.
Add cream and flour.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into greased and floured tube cake pan.
Bake 1 hour at 275°, then 30 minutes on 300°.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Beat together margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs and vanilla. Add combined flour, soda, salt and cinnamon. Mix well. Stir in oats and raisins. Drop by tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: curry dip
directions: Stir together curry powder, salt and mustard.
Gradually whisk in the mayonnaise, keeping smooth.
Whisk in onion and Tabasco. Chill, covered tightly, for 2 hours or overnight so flavor has time to develop thoroughly.
Makes 3/4 cup.

title: senate bean soup
directions: Simmer beans and ham in water for 2 hours.
Add remaining ingredients and cook at least 1 more hour.
Take meat off ham bones; dice and add to soup.
Season to taste.
Mash beans slightly to thicken or can add some instant mashed potatoes.

title: peppers and pasta
directions: Heat oil in skillet; add garlic.
Saute until golden brown. Add sliced peppers.
Cook until they begin to brown (keep warm for serving).
Meantime, cook and drain pasta.
Pour garlic-pepper mixture over drained pasta.
Sprinkle with parsley and cheese. Toss gently to mix.
Serve hot with garlic bread.

title: crunchy frozen punch-slush
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in boiling water.
Bring to a boil. Set aside to cool.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Before baking biscuits, put the melted Crisco on top of biscuits.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Peel onions and slice into rings. Saute sliced onions in the butter for 15 to 20 minutes or until clear.
Put half of the onions into a casserole.
Top with half of the crumbs and sprinkle with the cheese. Repeat layers, ending with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, in a 325° oven about 30 minutes.

title: black pudding
directions: Mix boiling water
and soda.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Steam 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with hard sauce.

title: nacho dip supreme
directions: In saucepan, combine all ingredients. Heat just until cheese melts, stirring frequently.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.
You can also melt the ingredients in the microwave.

title: pineapple applesauce cake
directions: Blend sugar, eggs and shortening together.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add applesauce and pineapple to batter, then add nuts, raisins and fruit.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 2 hours.

title: cucumber sauce for salmon
directions: Peel cucumber, cut in half and seed.
Dice the seeded cucumber.
In pan cook cucumber and water (shaking or stirring to prevent burning) for 2 to 3 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Put cucumber in bowl and add rest of ingredients.
Stir and cool.
Cook salmon in your favorite way.
Serve with sauce.

title: white pizza
directions: Prepare shell as asked.
Then add your garlic on top (add more by taste).
Sprinkle with salt.
Spread Mozzarella cheese all over, then add the tomato, diced in small chunks, all over.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Cut and serve.

title: dutch meat loaf
directions: Lightly mix beef, bread crumbs, 1/2 can tomato sauce, egg, salt and pepper.
Shape into loaf in shallow pan.
Combine remaining sauce with rest of ingredients.
Pour over loaf.
Baste several times during baking.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: five flavor pound cake(chemist's delight)
directions: Cream the margarine, Crisco and sugar well.
Add unbeaten eggs.
Mix well.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add flavorings and mix well.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: peppered pita toasts
directions: About 5 minutes before serving, preheat broiler if manufacturer directs.
Slice each pita horizontally in half; spread cut sides with softened butter or margarine.
Cut each half in thirds.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Cream 3/4 c sugar and shortening till light and fluffy.
Add egg; beat well.
Stir together 2 c flour, the baking powder, and 1/4 tsp salt.
Add flour mixture and milk alternately to creamed mixture.
Beat till smooth after each addition.
Spread in greased 8-inch sq or 9-inch sq baking pan.
Top with blueberries.
Combine 1/2 c sugar, the remaining 1/2 c flour and cinnamon; cut in butter or margarine till crumbly.
Sprinkle over berries.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 min.
Cut into squares.
Serve warm.
Makes 1 coffee cake.

title: krusty korn kobs
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease iron corn molds using pastry brush.
Grease well.
Place in oven while mixing ingredients. Mold must be hot.
Mix ingredients as listed.
Mix well and pour into hot molds, filling 1/2 full.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375°.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix 4 cups flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, sugar and caraway seed.
Add and separate raisins.
Add buttermilk; mix.

title: christmas wreaths
directions: Melt first 4 ingredients in double boiler.
Add cereal and stir until well coated.
Butter fingers and form wreaths on wax paper.
Decorate with 3 red hots per wreath.
Let sit overnight.

title: angel fuzz
directions: Cream together cream cheese and Cool Whip. Set aside.
Drain mandarin oranges, pineapple chunks and cherries. Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Add mini-marshmallows.
Add 1/2 cup walnuts if desired.
Chill 1 hour.

title: cheese balls
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix with chives, garlic salt and Accent. Chop beef in blender. Add about 1/3 of the beef to cream cheese and mix well.
Sprinkle the remainder of the beef on wax paper.
Form cheese into ball and roll in remaining beef.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine ground beef, 1/2 package bread crumbs, onion, bell pepper and eggs.
Fry in large frying pan until done.
Remove from pan.
Add gravy mix in frying pan.
Prepare according to package directions, then place salisbury steak back into pan and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Sift together and set aside flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Blend together shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour mixture and mix well.
Add oatmeal and vanilla and chocolate chips; dough will be crumbly. Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Makes 11 dozen.

title: coconut balls
directions: Cream oleo and powdered sugar.
Mix in Eagle Brand, coconut and pecans.
Roll mixture into balls and freeze.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips.
Dip frozen balls in chocolate mixture. Place on waxed paper.

title: eggs and asparagus
directions: Cook asparagus (don't overcook).
Drain.
Cut up whites of eggs.
Add the rest; heat and serve on toast.
Grate yellows of eggs and put on top of each serving.
(For family I often cut yellow with the whites.)

title: bishop's bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and shortening, blending with fork. Save 3/4 cup of this mixture for top crumbs.
To remainder, add baking powder, soda, egg, sour milk and cinnamon.
Beat briskly until smooth.
Put into greased pan and scatter crumb mixture on top.
Bake 25 minutes in hot oven (400°).
Bake in loaf or 9 x 9-inch pan.
Serve with honey.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Blend cottage cheese and buttermilk.
Add other ingredients and blend.
Chill.
Use with raw vegetables or crackers.

title: behthia's custard pie
directions: Beat together.
Sprinkle nutmeg.
Bake at 475° for 5 minutes and 425° for 10 minutes.

title: almond bark candy
directions: Melt almond bark in very cool oven (200°) in cake pan for 1/2 hour.
Put almond bark in a large bowl (stainless steel works best) and set in hot water. Add cereal, nuts and marshmallows. Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: dill dip
directions: Stir well!
Enjoy!
This is wonderful with fresh raw veggies.

title: bean relish
directions: Mix together. Chill and serve.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Note:
Add as many different meats as you like.

title: bread stuffing
directions: Combine butter, onion and celery in a bowl.
Microwave for 10 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Makes enough for stuffing 5 to 6 pound roasting chicken.

title: lighthouse egg
directions: Butter both sides of bread.
Cut out center of bread in the shape of a circle, about 1 1/2 inches in diameter (one way is to use the cover of a pill bottle).
Put bread in frying pan.
Break egg and place in hole in center of bread.
Fry bread on both sides until egg is thoroughly cooked (yolk no longer runs).
Use low flame.
Remove from pan and eat.
Enjoy!

title: irish tea cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Combine shortening, sugar and egg.
Combine slowly; alternate flour and milk.
Add other ingredients.

title: glazed ham loaf
directions: Combine ham, veal, egg, 1 cup orange juice, salt, pepper and crumbs.
Shape and bake in 350° oven, in shallow dish, basting often with 1/2 of glaze, for 1 1/2 hours.
Ten minutes before ham has finished cooking, top with orange slices.

title: cream cheese frosting for coconut cake
directions: Melt butter in skillet, add coconut and simmer on low heat, stirring until golden brown.
Remove from skillet and place on absorbent paper to cool.
Blend 2 Tbsp. butter with cream cheese and vanilla, add milk and sugar alternately, beating well.	Stir in 1-3/4 c. coconut.
Frost cake and sprinkle remaining coconut on top.

title: mayo-parmesan bread
directions: Preheat broiler.
Cut bread loaf crosswise in half.
Reserve half for another use.
Cut remaining bread portion lengthwise in half.
Place pieces, cut side up, on the unheated rack of the broiler pan, then set aside.

title: cranberry sauce bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
In mixing bowl, beat together eggs, sugar and cranberry sauce until well blended.
Stir in melted butter and orange juice.
Stir in flour mixture until just moistened.
Fold in nuts and orange rind.
Do not overbeat. Spread into greased loaf pan and bake in 350°
oven for 55 to 60 minutes, or in 5 (3 x 6-inch) tiny loaf pans for 40 minutes.
Let stand about 15 minutes and turn loaves out onto wire rack to finish cooling.
Store in refrigerator or freezer.

title: asparagus rolls(appetizer)
directions: Cut crusts off bread; roll flat.
Mix Blue cheese, cream cheese and 1 egg.
Spread cream cheese mixture on bread.
Roll bread slice around asparagus spear.
Dip in butter and sesame seed.
Cut in bite size pieces (4 per slice).
Freeze on tray, then put in container until needed.
Bake from freezer 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.

title: spiced zesta crackers
directions: Put all ingredients into gallon jar.
Rotate jar until crackers are covered in the ingredients.

title: cherry torta
directions: Mix like pie crust and pack in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Take out and crumble while warm.
Put back
into pan and pat down solid.
Cool.

title: spicy korean beef
directions: Combine soy sauce, garlic powder, salt and peppers.
Slowly whisk in the oil.
Place beef in a plastic bag.
Pour sauce over meat.
Seal bag and refrigerate for 6 hours.
Turn bag occasionally.
Drain meat and discard marinade.
Cook meat as you desire.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Press into baking dish.
Coat with ketchup.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hamburger-bean hash
directions: Mix hamburger and onions, salt and pepper.
Cook until brown. Add potatoes, tomato sauce (rinse can with a little water).
Cook until potatoes are soft.
Add pork and beans (medium can).
Simmer all together at least 15 minutes or until ready to eat.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients; mix milk, oil and egg and add to dry ingredients.
Mix lightly; add blueberries.
Do not beat! Heat oven to 400°.
Spray pan with Pam.
Bake 25 to 28 minutes.

title: big thelma's punch
directions: Heat sugar and water until sugar is dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients and enough water to make 1 gallon punch.

title: fruity jello jigglers
directions: Follow directions on boxes of Jell-O Jigglers.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill for 1 hour, then add oranges.
Chill for 3 more hours.
Cut into squares or make your own shapes.

title: german apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with a spoon.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Easy and yummy! I sprinkle powdered sugar on top.
No icing needed.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix flour, oleo and chopped nuts together and spread in 13 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until lightly browned.
Let cool.

title: all-in-one potato and hamburg
directions: In shallow Pyrex pan, layer potatoes, hamburg and soup.
Mix bread crumbs and cheese; sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: tangy broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise or Miracle Whip, sugar and vinegar in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Refrigerate. Serves 8.

title: pete's crab cakes
directions: In a large skillet, saute onion and celery in 1 tablespoon butter for 3 minutes.
In a medium bowl, combine onion and celery mixture, crab meat, 3/4 cup bread crumbs, mayonnaise, egg, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Mix well and shape into 4 patties.
Coat with remaining 1/2 cup bread crumbs, pressing crumbs into patties.
In same large skillet over medium heat, melt remaining 4 tablespoons butter.
Fry patties in butter until golden brown on both sides, about 8 to 9 minutes total.
Makes 4 crab cakes.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Cream together cheese, mayonnaise, wine and mustard.
Add all seasonings.
Fold in crab meat.
Transfer to 9 x 12-inch Pyrex or Corning dish.
Bake in 350° oven until brown on top, about 40 minutes.
Serve warm with crackers, biscuits or dark breads. Serves 15 to 20 as hors d'oeuvres.

title: petite cheesecakes
directions: You will need 24 miniature cupcake liners.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Drain.
Place in baking dish.
Add Tater Tots (tumbled).
In a separate bowl, mix soup and milk. Pour mixture over Tater Tots and meat.
Tumble again.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple stack cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease seven 8-inch round pans and line bottoms with waxed paper; set aside.

title: wienie lottas
directions: Cook tortillas in water according to package.
Combine next 3 ingredients.
Place a hot dog in each tortilla; top with 2 tablespoons chili mix.
Roll tortillas around franks.
Arrange seam down in a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine remaining chili mixture and tomato sauce.
Pour over tortilla.
Sprinkle with cheese (after baking).
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: red cinnamon apples
directions: After cooking apples in syrup, strain syrup to take pieces of apple, etc. from it.
Take 2 cups of the syrup and add tapioca. Stir until thickened.
Will thicken more when cold.
Spoon over apples.
Top with whipped cream and cherry and fresh mint leaves.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine soups, garlic salt, tomatoes and chicken.
Mix well. Soak Doritos in broth.
Line bottom of buttered casserole with Doritos, a layer of onions, chicken mixture and then a layer of cheese.
Repeat second layer.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until cheese is bubbly, but not brown.

title: hello dollies
directions: Combine melted butter and graham crackers.
Press into bottom of 8 x 8 inch pan.
Mix other ingredients together, except Eagle Brand milk, and pour on top of crushed graham crackers.
Now pour Eagle Brand milk over all of it.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: In a saucepan, combine first 4 ingredients.
Bring to boiling, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat.
Cook and stir for 4 to 5 minutes or until thick.

title: zucchini cheese bake
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish.
Layer zucchini, onions and cheese until all are used.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and add more cheese on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes to one hour.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Slit each peeled shrimp along back edge.
Dry shrimp well on paper towels.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan, adding salt, garlic and tablespoon of chopped parsley.
Arrange shrimp in single layer and bake uncovered for 5 minutes.
Turn and baste shrimp cooking on both sides.
Sprinkle shrimp with lemon zest, lemon juice and remaining parsley.
Bake until shrimp is pink and tender.
Do not overbake.
Serve with rice and garnish with remaining parsley.

title: blueberry dream dessert(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Mix oatmeal, flour and brown sugar.
Add melted butter; mix well.
Line bottom of 8-inch square pan, reserving about 1/2 cup for topping.
Spread pie filling on crust.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cabbage patch soup
directions: Combine all but carrots and peppers. Cook on low 7 to 8 hours. Add vegetables.

title: the p.b.j.  sandwich
directions: Mix in small bowl peanut butter and cinnamon.
Put the peanut butter and cinnamon on a slice of bread.
Then put jelly on the other slice of bread.
Put it together and eat.
Serves one.

title: chicken marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients and marinate chicken for 1 to 2 hours. Grill as usual.

title: spinach linguini or tortellini with tomato sauce
directions: Cook tortellini or linguini according to package directions; drain.
Spoon onto warm platter.

title: barbara's chili recipe #1
directions: Cook beef, pepper, onion and garlic.
Stir in chili powder. Cook 1 minute.
Drain and chop tomatoes.
Add tomatoes, A.1. sauce and water.
Heat to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add beans.
Top with cheese.

title: verna kate's sweet potato pie
directions: Bake potatoes at 400° until tender.
Cool.
Remove skins. Mash or whip potatoes in large mixing bowl.
Add butter, sugar, salt and extracts.
Set aside.
In small bowl, beat egg yolks slightly.
Add to potato mixture with milk/cream.
Set aside. Whip egg whites until soft peaks form.
Fold gently into potato mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes; reduce temperature to 350°.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until center is cooked.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Cut in shortening.
Add water slowly while kneading until soft dough is formed.
Divide dough into 12 to 14 balls.
Roll out each on a lightly floured board to form a 6-inch circle.
Bake on ungreased griddle until lightly browned on each side.
Keep dough covered while rolling out tortillas.

title: texas coleslaw
directions: Combine milk, sugar, salt and pepper; mix well.
Gradually add vinegar, stirring constantly.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Prepare One Bowl Brownies as directed using 4 eggs.
Spread into prepared pan.

title: italian turkey pie
directions: Combine turkey, milk, bread crumbs, garlic powder and 1/2 teaspoon oregano.
Press into 9-inch pie pan, bringing up on sides.
Spread tomato paste evenly over "crust."
Top with 1/2 teaspoon oregano, mushrooms and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese, green peppers and olives.
Bake an additional 15 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes before cutting into wedges.

title: hearty minestrone soup
directions: Place broth, water, tomatoes, basil, oregano and pepper in 4-quart saucepan.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Meanwhile, drain and rinse beans well under cold water in a colander.
Add beans, onion, carrot, garlic, peas and macaroni to the boiling broth. Reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, until macaroni is cooked, about 12 to 15 minutes.
Divide cheese among 6 bowls; pour piping hot soup over cheese.
Serve with Italian bread and a salad.
Makes 6 servings.

title: party punch
directions: Combine four ingredients first and
chill.
Add
ginger ale just before serving and serve with ice.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs and sugar well.
Pour milk into sugar and eggs.
Add flavor.
Melt the butter; add to mixture.
Pour into pie crust; sprinkle nutmeg on top of custard.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until custard will be shaky but will be firm when it cools.

title: fruit pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix with eggs and sugar.
Stir in coconut, pecans and vinegar.
Pour into 2 pie shells.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: five can casserole
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Place in casserole.
Empty soups on top; add vegetables with liquid.
Add 1/2 chow mein noodles and stir with soups.
Top with more noodles.
Heat 30 minutes in 325° oven.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and onions until tender.
Drain, combine with cooked rice and mix with 1 cup of cheese. Spread one cup of cheese on top.
Bake in 350 degree oven until cheese melts.

title: cream cheese puffs(serves 10 to 12)
directions: Make 4 bread rounds per slice of bread (about the size of a shot glass).
Butter rounds, toast one side.
(Place in oven for 3 to 5 minutes.)
Put well blended mixture of cream cheese, mayonnaise, green onions, Tabasco and Parmesan cheese on each round.
Can now be frozen.

title: shrimply divine dip
directions: Blend cream cheese with remainder of ingredients.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.
Serve with snack crackers (preferably not too strongly flavored crackers).

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Prepare crust.
In mixer bowl beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in milk until smooth, then eggs and vanilla.
Toss 1/2 cup chips with flour; add to cheese mixture. Pour into pan over crust.
Sprinkle remaining chips over top. Bake 1 hour or until center is set.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except potato chips.
Put into casserole dish and cover with crushed potato chips. Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: baked fish fillets
directions: Cut fillets into serving pieces.
Combine milk and salt.
Dip fish into milk, then into crumbs, being sure fish is completely covered with crumbs.
Place in a greased baking dish or ovenproof platter; sprinkle with oil and brown quickly in very hot oven, 500°, for 10 to 20 minutes.
Do not add water.
Serve with almond butter sauce, melted butter or lemon butter.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed. Melt butter in rice.
Cook broccoli in salt water and drain; add milk, soup, rice and cheese in casserole dish.
Stir slightly.
Put bread crumbs on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Beat eggs well.
Cream sugar, margarine and Crisco.
Add beaten eggs to creamed mixture.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Alternate flour mixture and milk.
Add flavorings. Once you begin to beat the batter, do so continually until all ingredients have been added.
Pour into pound cake pan and place in a cold oven.
Turn oven to 310° and bake about 1 1/4 hours, depending on the weight of your pan.

title: chicken stew
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
While chicken is cooling, cook potatoes and other vegetables until tender, then drain water and add vegetables to chicken broth.
Debone chicken and add to broth. Add the bouillon cubes.
Let simmer 30 minutes.
Serve with hot corn bread muffins.

title: deluxe scrambled eggs
directions: Microwave cream cheese and milk on High, 25 to 30 seconds. Add eggs; mix until blended.
Heat ham, onion and butter in pan. Add egg mixture. Cook.

title: best ever beans
directions: Cook ground beef and bacon; drain.
Combine remaining ingredients in a crock-pot.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.

title: grits casserole
directions: Prepare grits and cook according to directions.
While it is still hot, add butter, garlic cheese, Cheddar cheese and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well and pour into a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.
Wonderful on Christmas morning!

title: pretzel salad
