directions: Mix pretzels, butter and 3 tablespoons sugar; bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 400° for 7 minutes.
Cool crust.

title: mexican pie
directions: Bake pie shell according to directions for about 10 minutes. Brown ground beef. Add taco seasoning. In small bowl, mix beans and 1/4 cup salsa. Place bean mixture in pie shell. Top with about 15 crushed tortilla chips. Put ground beef on top of chips. Add grated cheese. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes. Serve with additional salsa and sour cream.

title: pink lady punch
directions: Stir together cranberry juice cocktail and sugar.
Add the pineapple juice (or grapefruit) and chill.
Pour into punch bowl and add ginger ale and Hawaiian Punch.
Float lime sherbet on top of punch.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Using a spoon, mix all ingredients, except blueberries.
Fold blueberries into batter.
Line muffin tins with paper cups.
Fill to 3/4 of paper liner.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: In 5-cup ice cream maker, combine all ingredients except milk. Add milk to bring mixture up to fill line.
Add more milk if necessary; freeze.
Makes 8 servings.

title: fried mushrooms
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper in a small bowl.
Set aside. Combine eggs, 1 1/2 teaspoons oil and water; mix well.
Clean mushrooms with damp paper towels.
Dredge mushrooms in flour mixture and dip in egg mixture.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Chill at least 1 1/2 hours.
Deep fry mushrooms in hot oil (375°) until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve mushrooms.

title: low-fat chocolate brownies
directions: Beat margarine at medium speed of an electric mixer until fluffy.
Gradually add sugar and beat well.
Add egg whites, sour cream, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients; stir well.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Pour batter into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Yields 24 servings.
Spread Creamy Chocolate Frosting.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown onions in seasoning until golden brown.
Add meat and brown.
Add tomatoes, tomato puree, chili powder and salt.
Cover and cook slowly for 20 minutes.
Add kidney beans and cook 10 minutes.
Add water if mixture seems dry.

title: almost homemade peach cobbler
directions: In a large skillet, combine peaches, nutmeg, cinnamon, sugar and butter or margarine.
Cut one pie crust into squares about 1-inch in size.
Add to peaches and cook on low heat for 10 minutes; stir as needed.
Remove from heat.
Remove other pie crust from pan and flatten, then place crust over peach mixture. Place in oven and cook for 15 minutes at 350° to 400°.
Top crust should be lightly browned after cooking.

title: apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Stir sugar, flour, spice and salt together.
Mix lightly with the apples.
Turn into pastry lined pan.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Weave lattice on top crust; seal and flute the edges.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Remove from the oven; sprinkle with the cheese.

title: strawberry salad(serves 12)
directions: Mix jello and boiling water.
Add pineapple, frozen strawberries and pecans.
Pour 1/2 mixture into flat square container (8 x 8-inch).
Chill until firm.
Cover with sour cream and add last 1/2 of strawberry mixture.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce leaf with your favorite fruit dressing.

title: jim's mocha oreo dessert
directions: Combine cookie crumbs and butter and press gently into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate.
When chilled, spoon on softened ice cream and freeze.
Melt chocolate and 2 tablespoons butter. Add sugar, salt and milk. Bring mixture to a boil, stirring until thickened.
(Be careful, it burns easily.)
Remove from heat and add vanilla. Chill and spread on top of ice cream. Freeze.
Whip the cream. Add Kahlua (or coffee) and powdered sugar. Spread over chocolate layer and sprinkle with nuts.
Freeze again. Cut in squares to serve.

title: easy soup
directions: Combine soups and cream.
Do not boil.
Add crab meat and simmer 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add cooking sherry and sprinkle paprika on top of each bowl.

title: kool-aid ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into ice cream churn.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix all ingredients together except whipped cream.
Let stand for 24 hours.
Fold in whipped cream; let stand 30 minutes and serve.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: easy kosher dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers...dry well...pack in clean sterile jars.

Boil watah, vinegar, salt 'n spices 'n pore over cucumbers in jar...let set a few minutes 'n pore back in pan 'n boil again...pore rite back over cucumbers...add 3 buds garlic 1 head dill 'n 1 bay leaf to each jar...put lids on 'n seal.
The reason fur porin' liquid over cucumbers twice iz to get the jar 'n contents hot...the second heatin' will assure thet the jar will seal.

title: banana punch
directions: Combine sugar and water; bring to a boil for about 3 minutes; cool to room temperature.
Combine sugar syrup, pineapple juice, orange juice, bananas, and lemon juice.
Chill.

This may be prepared well in advance and frozen in cartons or Ziploc bags. When ready to serve, have punch base removed from freezer and almost thawed or take chilled punch base from refrigerator; add chilled ginger ale and serve.
This will serve 35 to 40 punch cups.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in casserole.
Place Swiss cheese slices over chicken to cover.
Mix water and soup together and pour over cheese and chicken.
Sprinkle chopped onions, melted butter and toss with dressing.
Mix and sprinkle all over the top.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Yields 4 servings.

title: strawberry spring delight
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese. Add topping. Mix well. Break angel food cake into small pieces and add to whipped topping mixture. Mix well. Put into 9 x 13 baking dish. Mix strawberries and glaze
and spread over cake mixture. Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: pea salad
directions: Drain peas and mix with eggs and vegetables.
Add mayonnaise, salt and pepper to taste.
Chill before serving.

title: banana health frappe
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Cover and blend about 7 seconds.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch baking pan in 350° oven as it preheats.
Remove pan from oven and add crumbs.
Stir into butter. Mix and pat out in an even layer.
Sprinkle nuts, chips and coconut evenly in layers.
Drizzle or spoon milk over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Partially cool and cut into squares.

title: glazed cornish hens
directions: Combine 1/4 cup of jelly and cinnamon in a small saucepan; heat, stirring until melted.
Set aside.
Place hen halves, skin side up, on rack in shallow roasting pan.
Sprinkle with salt. Roast in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Brush with jelly-cinnamon mixture and roast 25 to 30 minutes longer or until browned and tender.

title: sour cream muffins
directions: Cream sugar and margarine well.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Add sour cream and blend well.
Gradually add dry ingredients.
Beat until blended.
Fill paper muffin cups 2/3 full.
Top with lots of sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 18 muffins.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook whole chicken until done; cool and debone.
Set aside. Save broth from chicken.
Add chicken back to broth after deboning.
Add salt, pepper and butter.
Keep on low heat.

title: coconut balls
directions: Combine egg, sugar, dates and shortening in a saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, at medium heat 5 to 7 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cool and form into balls and roll in coconut.

title: dove breast hors d'oeuvres
directions: You will need toothpicks soaked in water.

title: angie russo's "s" cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add margarine and mix thoroughly.
Add milk, eggs and vanilla.
Roll small amounts in narrow rope (about 1/2-inch) and cut into 3 to 4-inch lengths.
Dip one side into cinnamon/sugar mixture on flat plate.
Shape into 5-inch shape and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven about 15 minutes.
Don't overbake.
Cool on rack.
These cookies keep well.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip muffins
directions: Mix until moistened.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full (either sprayed or paper lined).
Bake at 400° for 17 to 20 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Put diced apples in large mixing bowl; add unbeaten eggs and stir until well blended.
Add salad oil and mix again.
Combine dry ingredients and add to apple mixture.
Fold together until all dry ingredients are gone.
Add vanilla and nuts.
This will be very thick.
Pour into greased 9 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch baking dish. Bake for 1 hour at 325°; if glass pan is used, bake at 300°.

title: southern chicken patties
directions: Make a cream sauce with margarine, flour and 1 3/4 cups milk. Combine chicken, 1/2 cup cracker crumbs, parsley, seasonings and 1 cup sauce.
Mix well.
Chill for about 5 minutes.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Sprinkle some pecans in bottom of a well-greased 10-inch Bundt pan.
Combine sugar, cinnamon and remaining pecans.
Cut biscuits into quarters; roll each piece in sugar mixture and layer in pan. Combine brown sugar and butter; pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Invert onto a serving plate.

title: teresa's yeast rolls
directions: Mix yeast and warm water.
Set aside and let rise.
In another bowl, combine hot water, sugar and shortening.
Add egg and yeast. Slowly add flour.
Beat until mix gets thick and slows mixer. Put dough in greased bowl and let stand, covered with towel, until it rises for 2 hours.
Then pinch rolls off dough and put in pan. Let rise again.
Cook at 425° until golden brown.

title: the cooper family's applesauce
directions: First peel 4 to 6 apples (more or less) depending on number of people to be served.
Slice into a saucepan into medium to thin slices until all apples are cut up.
Next add just a little water, enough to cover bottom of pan.
(When apples start cooking, then will make enough liquid.)
Add a pinch of nutmeg.
Sprinkle some cinnamon and sugar over apples.
Stir and cover, cooking over medium; lower after comes to a boil.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally until all apples are softened and there is a sauce consistency.

Taste test and add more cinnamon and sugar if needed. Sometimes we use a potato masher when apples are getting soft and mushy to break up the chunks or if you like chunky style, do not mash but only stir.

title: no bake peanut butter bars
directions: Mix and put into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt 2 cups milk chocolate chips and spread on top.
Cut into squares.

title: dinette cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour pan (8 x 8 x 2-inches); (9 x 9 x 2-inches), or round pan (9 x 1 1/2-inches).
Beat all ingredients in a large mixer bowl on low speed, scraping bowl constantly, 30 seconds.
Beat on high speed, scraping bowl occasionally, 3 minutes.
Pour into pan.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean; square (35 to 40 minutes); round (35 minutes).
Cool.

title: mini butterscotch phyllo cups
directions: **Phyllo cups (Athens Food brand in freezer section).

title: swiss steak
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Bake pork steak in a wine-mushroom sauce for company dinner.
Brown steaks in heavy skillet; season and top with sliced onions.
Mix Sauterne with undiluted mushroom soup and pour around meat.
Cover and bake until tender.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Bake in ungreased 9 x 12-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve with or without Cool Whip.

title: mexican hot mouth
directions: In a large skillet, brown the meat and onion. Drain well.
In a large baking dish or an ovenproof skillet, add meat, corn, beans, water, taco seasoning and salsa.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Top with cheese when done.
Serves 6.
Add additional salsa, if needed.

title: egg salad
directions: Mash hard-boiled eggs.
Blend with salad dressing.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add onions, if desired.
Serve on sandwiches.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Heat the clam juice, water and chicken concentrate in a saute pan.
You will need 4 cups of liquid.
Heat the empty casserole in oven at 375°.
Melt butter in a large heavy frying pan; heat to sizzle.
Add rice and stir constantly until golden.
Place rice in heated casserole and add hot bouillon.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Add baked rice and stir parsley, onion, nuts, garlic and shrimp.
Mix well.
Replace cover and cook 15 minutes longer.
Use McCormick crab and shrimp boil to boil the shrimp. Replace cover and cook 20 minutes longer.

title: benne seed cookies(sesame)
directions: Brown Benne seed in slow oven 15 minutes.
Mix all ingredients.
Drop 1/2 teaspoon on greased tray approximately 1-inch apart.
Bake 10 minutes at 325°.
Cool slightly.
Remove with spatula.

title: double flaky apple pie
directions: To make a flaky double crust: combine flour and salt in mixing bowl.
Cut in Crisco with a pastry blender.	Mixture should be fairly course.
Sprinkle with water (a tablespoon a time) and mix lightly with a fork.
When all water has been added, work dough into a firm ball.
Divide dough into 2 parts and press each part into flat circles with smooth edges.
On a lightly floured board, roll bottom crust into a circle 1/8 inch thick and 1 1/2 inches larger than a pie plate.
Trim edge evenly with plate and add the apple filling.
Wet rim of crust, then add the top crust and fold under the bottom crust.
Bake 30-40 minutes at 400°.

title: bachelor potatoes
directions: Line a 9 x 13 pan with foil.
Layer potatoes, onions, cheese, margarine, salt and pepper.
Seal foil.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Place margarine, apricot nectar, salt, pepper and thyme into frypan.
Let this come to a boil and add chicken strips.
Simmer for 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.
Turn several times.
Put lid on frypan.

title: hornets nest cake
directions: Cook pudding according to directions. Dump cake mix into warm pudding.
Grease an oblong pan. Pour mixture into pan, and then sprinkle butterscotch chips & pecans on cake. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ricotta cheese cake
directions: Mix cake as directed; pour into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix until smooth the Ricotta, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Pour mixture over the cake batter evenly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
When cool, top with pie filling and Cool Whip.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and add other ingredients.
Put in Pyrex dish and cover with 1 cup stuffing mix and margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked acorn squash
directions: Cut squash in half and remove seed, etc. Cut enough off bottom to make flat to stand. Put salt, pepper and butter inside. Mix together remaining ingredients. Fill squash; dot with margarine. Place in pan with 1/4 inch water in bottom. Cover and bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes to 1 hour or until tender. (Can add chopped apples to mixture.)

title: governor's chicken casserole
directions: Mix and bake in greased casserole at 350° for 1 hour.
Last 15 minutes top with potato chips or buttered bread crumbs and brown.

title: lazy-daisy cake(shortcake)
directions: Heat milk and butter.
Set aside.
Beat eggs, then add sugar. Mix flour and baking powder, separately.
Add flour mixture to egg mixture alternately with hot milk, then add vanilla.
Bake in a flat pan (8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch) for 30 minutes at 375° (moderate oven).

title: jello cake
directions: Follow directions for baking cake on the cake box.
Let cake cool, then prick all over top with fork.
Mix 1 large box jello using only 3 cups boiling water.
Mix well until jello is dissolved.
Let jello mixture cool.
Pour slowly over top of cake. Set in refrigerator until jello sets.
Mix instant pudding and spread over top of cake.
Top with Cool Whip spread over the pudding.
Chill.
Keep in refrigerator.
Serve.
This makes a cool refreshing dessert.

title: spanish rice
directions: Wash rice.
Fry rice in oil until browned.
Add cumin, garlic powder, tomato sauce, chicken broth, water, salt and pepper.
Cook on low heat, until rice is tender.

title: sweet yogurt dressing
directions: Heat the 2 cups water in a large pot until boiling.
Add vegetables, cover and cook until tender (about 10 minutes.)
Blend vegetables with part of the cooking water in a blender or food processor.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Blend ingredients in saucepan over low heat. Remove.
Let cool.
Use as a marinade for beef, pork, fish or poultry.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Spread pecan halves in single layer on sided cookie sheet. Put pats of margarine on pecans.
Drizzle corn syrup over this. Roast at 250° to 300° for 1 hour until slightly brown, stirring occasionally.
Pour out on brown paper and salt.

title: cheese rolls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Shape into rolls and roll in chili powder.

title: chewy fudge squares
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in large saucepan.
Add sugar.
Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, salt and nuts.
Stir just until smooth.
Spread mixture evenly onto a lightly-greased jelly roll pan.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs in large bowl.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add to oil mixture.
Then add the apples, nuts and lemon peel.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate cream roll
directions: Beat until thick the egg yolks, sugar, chocolate, flour, baking powder and salt.
Fold in egg whites and vanilla.
Bake in a 10 x 15-inch pan, greased with waxed paper 10 to 15 minutes at 400°.
When it comes out of the oven, place on a towel with powdered sugar spread on it.
Cut the ends.
When cool, spread whipped cream over and roll.
Place in refrigerator.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and green pepper.
Add seasonings, tomato sauce and catsup.
Pour into baking dish and add sliced or grated cheese to cover the top.
Place biscuits on top of cheese and bake at 375°
for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: yeast bread
directions: In one bowl, dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
In second bowl, mix shortening, sugar and salt. Add boiling water; mix well. Add eggs and mix well.
Add flour and yeast mixture alternately to shortening mixture.
Let rise until double in size.

title: company carrots
directions: Saute the carrots and onions.
When almost tender, add the rest of the ingredients.
Steam for a few minutes covered, over low heat, until carrots are tender.

title: pasta and broccoli
directions: Chop broccoli; set aside.
Cook and stir garlic in hot oil in skillet over medium-high heat, until lightly browned.
Add broccoli; cook and stir for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add American/Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese, butter and broth. Stir.
Simmer until cheese melts.
Pour sauce over ziti in a large bowl.
Toss gently to coat.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in water until done.
Save the broth.
In a bowl, mix 1/2 of dressing mix with chicken broth until moistened.
Put mixture in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix both cans of soup and milk together.
Add chicken that has been cut into pieces. Pour chicken mixture on top of dressing.
Put remaining dry dressing on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until dressing has browned.

title: christmas cutout butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Use enough flour to make a stiff dough. For a softer cookie, don't roll out too thin.

title: pastel clouds
directions: Prepare cake mix and add 1/2 package of Jell-O before beating. Bake in cupcake pans according to directions on cake mix package. Cool 10 minutes in pans.
Remove from pans; cool on racks. Dissolve remaining Jell-O in boiling water.
Cream butter; add part of the sugar gradually, blending after each addition.
Add remaining sugar alternately with Jell-O mixture, beating until smooth.
Spread on cupcakes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; debone and cut into small pieces.
In casserole dish, layer first half of dressing, mixed with butter, in bottom of dish.
Next, add layer of chicken.
Next, mix cream of celery soup and one cup of chicken broth together; pour over chicken. Next, layer other half of dressing over soup, saving 1/2 cup for top.
Repeat with mushroom soup and broth (mixed) and chicken. Top with 1/2 cup dressing.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Do not overcook.

title: ham and lima bean salad
directions: Cook limas according to package directions.
Drain.
Rinse with cold water.
Drain again.
In mixing bowl, combine beans, mushrooms, onion, ham, olives, parsley and pimento.

title: lazy day lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Brown your beef and add spaghetti sauce, set aside. Cook your noodles (about 12). Grease large rectangle pan. Next, layer your ingredients, noodles first, then sauce, then cheese. Keep layering until you run out. Then bake for 45 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream(vanilla)
directions: Beat eggs and mix in remaining ingredients.
Using whole milk, fill freezer to fill line.
This recipe is for a 1 gallon freezer. You may use fruit for different flavors.
Freeze according to freezer instructions.
We use table salt instead of ice cream salt (it is cheaper and freezes faster).

title: chow mein hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add all of the other ingredients except chow mein noodles.
Mix well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle with chow mein noodles.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: saucy meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, can of celery soup, egg, bread crumbs and salt and pepper to taste.
Scoop out with ice cream scoop.
Place on cookie sheet.
Cook in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until brown.
Take out of oven and place in casserole dish.
Pour 1 can of mushroom soup over meatballs.
Cover and return to oven for approximately 30 minutes.

title: idiot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup water.
Bring margarine, water and shortening to boil and cool in large bowl.
Mix eggs, sugar and 1 cup water.
Combine 3 mixtures, then add 7 cups of flour.
Mix and place in refrigerator until ready to use.
Two to three hours before using, roll out on floured surface and cut out fairly thin. Brush with melted butter.
Fold over and let rise until double in size and bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: wienies and kraut
directions: Bake wienies (split down the middle) and kraut until wienies are done and kraut is hot.
Place cheese in middle of wienies; continue baking until melted in a 350° oven.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Bring to a boil and pour over kraut mixture while very hot. Refrigerate overnight.
Serve cold.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Stir together.
Bake about 1 hour at 400° in sprayed pan. This is a good basic recipe that can be added with other ingredients which are very tasty.
Grated cheese adds a different flavor.
Let your taste buds run wild.

title: garden frittata
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, heat oil over medium heat until hot. Add potatoes, zucchini, green and red pepper, scallions and mushrooms.
Cook over medium heat, stirring often, until vegetables are soft, 5 to 8 minutes.
Spread vegetables in an even layer with back of spoon or fork.

title: chicken ashley
directions: Saute onions and garlic in 1 tablespoon oil until translucent. In a casserole dish, mix all the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until bubbly.
Serve over noodles or rice. Serves 4.

title: chalupa
directions: Cover meat with water.
Add all other ingredients.
Place on low heat for 6 hours.
Add water, if needed.
Should stay quite full.
Gets soupy.
Uncover after 6 hours and cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: no roll sugar cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, margarine, egg and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Mix with hands until dough can be gathered into a ball.
Pinch off pieces of dough and roll into balls about the size of a walnut.
Place on ungreased baking sheet, about 2-inches apart.
Dip bottom of glass (1 1/2-inch diameter) in granulated sugar.
Press each ball with glass until dough forms a circle.
Dip glass into sugar after each cookie is flattened.
Sprinkle additional sugar on cookies.
Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: peach pie cake
directions: Mix together the cake mix, eggs, lemon juice, nuts and peach pie filling.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan (greased and floured). Mix together the flour, margarine, sugar and lemon juice. Sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Pour pudding mix into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Stir in juice from pineapple, adding juice from oranges if necessary to make 1 cup liquid.
Set aside pineapple and oranges.

title: fruit balls
directions: In a blender or food processor, grind raisins, dates, figs and apricots.
Remove the seeds from the orange and grind the orange and rind separately.
Save some of the orange juice to use if needed.
Combine all ground ingredients.
Add just enough orange juice to soften.
Shape into small balls.
Roll in nuts.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.
Refrigerate.

title: jello angel pie
directions: Dissolve jello	in
1 cup boiling water.
Add 1 cup ice cubes and
water,
mixed.
Chill until syrupy, then whip.
Mix well chilled
evaporated
milk
with lemon juice and sugar and whip. Fold into jello.
Layer in 9 x 9-inch dish with vanilla wafers. Refrigerate.

title: cabbage and zucchini skillet
directions: Heat oil in large, heavy skillet and add cabbage.
Toss well with 2 wooden spoons.
Add onion and toss again.
Add liquid to skillet; reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add garlic and zucchini and cover again.
Simmer another 10 minutes.
Season to taste.

title: red rocker inn squash casserole
directions: Be sure squash is well drained.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well; form into balls. Brown on all sides. Drain; place in baking dish. Pour soup and water over balls. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: applesauce in the microwave
directions: Combine apples and water in 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with lid.
Microwave on High 10 to 12 minutes until apples are tender, stirring once.
Stir in sugar and cinnamon until blended. Process in blender until smooth.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix all together thoroughly.
Put in refrigerator in covered dish for 4 days.
Each day, mix well with hands.
Will be hard. On the fifth day, shape into logs and put on broiler pan.
Bake in oven for 8 hours at 150°.

title: pepper steak
directions: Combine soy sauce, garlic and ginger.
Add beef; toss and set aside.
While preparing veggies, heat oil in a large frying pan. Add beef; cook until brown.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes over low heat.
Turn heat up.
Add vegetables.
Toss until vegetables are tender, 10 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with water; add to pan. Stir and cook until thickened.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli, dressing, olives and seasoning; let set 15 minutes.
Drain off oil and keep in covered bowl until serving time.

title: mini sausage rolls
directions: Cut crescent roll dough into mini crescents, four mini crescents out of 1 roll.
Roll smokies in crescent.
Cook on cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes at 375 degrees.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Combine
sugar and cocoa powder in an ungreased 10-inch square glass
dish.
Drop butter onto sugar mixture.
Pour in milk.
Do not stir.
Microwave on High 2 to 3 minutes or until mixture
is bubbly.
Remove from oven and stir.
Stir in nuts and
vanilla. Spread
fudge
evenly
in
dish.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Cut into squares.

title: country buttercream ribbon chocolate fudge cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Combine cream cheese, eggs and sugar in a medium mixing bowl.
Beat at high speed with electric mixer until smooth.
Gradually add milk and next 3 ingredients, beating well.
Set aside.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Spread half of the chocolate cake mixture in pan. Spoon cream cheese mixture evenly over chocolate batter.
Top with remaining cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool completely.
Spread favorite frosting over cake.
Yields 15 servings.

title: 20 minute chicken parmesan
directions: Dip chicken in egg mixture, then in bread crumbs.
Brown on each side in butter.
Cover with Prego sauce.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes on low. Sprinkle both cheeses on top.
Cover and simmer for 5 more minutes.
Serve over noodles.

title: pineapple sparkle punch
directions: Combine juices and sugar; chill several hours.
Place ice in a punch bowl and add juice mixture.
Slowly pour in ginger ale and carbonated water.
Float fruit slices on top.
Serves 75.

title: tater casserole
directions: Brown beef until just done.
Mix all ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, in 375° oven for about 20 minutes or until top browns.

title: far east fried rice
directions: Blend sugar and soy sauce.
Set aside.
Heat butter in small skillet.
Add egg and cook as for omelet.
Remove from skillet. Cut in 1/2 inch strips and set aside.
Heat oil in wok or large skillet.
Add garlic, onion and red pepper.
Stir-fry for 1 minute.
Add green onions and stir-fry for 1 minute longer.
Stir in soy sauce mixture and heat.
Garnish with egg strips.
Serve at once.
Serves 4.

title: winter vichyssoise
directions: In large heavy pot, cook leeks and onion in butter until soft, about 15 minutes (do not brown them).
Add potatoes and chicken stock.
Cook for 20 to 30 minutes, until potatoes are soft.
Add white pepper and salt to taste.
Blend in food processor or blender until very smooth or push through fine sieve.
Return to soup pot. Heat to boiling.
Add cream and wine.
Heat again, but do not boil. Taste and adjust seasoning.
Serve sprinkled generously with chives.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Heat soup and add cream cheese.
Stir until well blended. Remove from heat.
Add gelatine (dissolved in cold water) to mixture.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into large fish-shaped mold (lightly oiled) and refrigerate.
Good on crackers or may be eaten as a salad.

title: spanish pepper chicken
directions: Whirl peppercorns in blender container until crushed.
Add olives, garlic, lemon rind and olive oil; blend until thick and fairly smooth.
Spread olive mixture over chicken; place in shallow dish.
Chill for 2 hours.
Grill chicken on both sides for 30 to 40 minutes, or until tender.

title: lottie gardner's chocolate cake
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, eggs and shortening.
Cream.
Add hot water. Add flour, soda and salt.
Last add buttermilk.
Bake at 325° until done, about 45 minutes, in a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been greased and floured.
Top with chocolate icing.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until fluffy.
Combine together dry ingredients and beat into the butter-sugar mixture alternately with milk.
Beat only until smooth.
Pour into greased 10 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Spoon cherry pie filling over batter. Sprinkle with sugar, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: hard candies
directions: Cover and bring to a boil.
Remove cover and boil to 290° Add flavoring and food coloring of choice.
Pour on lightly oiled marble slab in small "patties".

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Reserve 1 cup of cake mix and 1/8 cup of melted butter.
Mix together remaining mix and 1/2 cup of melted butter and 1 slightly beaten egg.
Press (with hand) into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together pumpkin, evaporated milk and 2 slightly beaten eggs.
Pour into pan.
Take 1 cup cake mix and the 1/8 cup melted butter.
Mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle over cake.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: congealed strawberry salad
directions: Mix jello and water. Add strawberries with juice, pineapple with juice and bananas.
Pour half into dish.
Let set and leave the other half out.
Spread with sour cream when set, then pour the other half on top and let set.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together first 3 ingredients. Add: 3 cups quick oats, 1/2 cup nuts.

title: beef squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion together; drain.
Cook ground beef; drain off grease.
Mix together, then add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken fried round steak
directions: Pound steak to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into 6 pieces.
Stir together the egg and milk.
Combine cracker crumbs, salt and pepper.
Dip meat into egg mixture, then in crumbs.
In a 12-inch skillet, brown meat in hot oil.
Turn once; cover and cook over low heat for 45 to 50 minutes, until tender.

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine shredded cabbage, bell pepper, onion and pimentos. Boil remaining ingredients. Pour over shredded slaw mix. Refrigerate overnight. Will keep 7 to 8 days.

title: cherry limeade
directions: In a tall glass, add the cherry syrup. Squeeze lime and put into the glass. Pour in Sprite or Slice drink and add some ice. Add a cherry.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Put oil and margarine in heavy pot (or Dutch oven).
Heat.
Put flour and salt in bag and shake; add chicken breasts, shaking to cover.
Brown chicken breasts in oil and margarine at medium heat for about 5 minutes on each side.
Cook three at one time.
When all are browned, remove from pot.
Remove pot from heat.
Add bouillon and stir to remove browned bits from bottom of pan. Squeeze in juice of 2 lemons.
Return chicken breasts to pan; cover and return to heat.
Simmer for 20 minutes until tender.

title: quicky vegetable soup(fast, cheap, easy)
directions: You can add some of the boiled potatoes and any leftover vegetable or meat.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Any combination of fresh fruit can be used. Combine fruits. Mix sour cream and mayonnaise. Fold in fruit. Add coconut, marshmallows and cherries.

title: fudgy brownie trifle
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of 13 x 9 x 2 pan. Stir brownie mix, water, oil and eggs in medium bowl until well blended.
Stir in coffee.
Spread in pan.
Bake 28 to 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted 2-inches from side of pan comes out clean.
Cool completely, about 1 hour.
Cut brownies into 1-inch squares.
Place half of the square in bottom of 3-quart glass bowl.
Make pudding mix as directed on package for pudding, using milk.
Pour half of the pudding over brownies in bowl.
Top with half each of the toffee bits and whipped topping.
Repeat with remaining brownies, pudding, toffee bits and whipped topping. Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: corn cakes
directions: Mix and bake in 450° oven.
For muffins, 10 to 15 minutes. For cornbread, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: bleu cheese dressing
directions: Blend sour cream and seasonings.
Stir in mayonnaise and blend at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Crumble in Bleu cheese and blend at medium speed for no longer than 4 minutes.
Refrigerate 24 hours before using.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: dinette cake
directions: Beat all ingredients in large mixer bowl on low speed, scraping bowl constantly, 30 seconds.
Beat on high speed, scraping bowl occasionally, 3 minutes.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Heat oven to 350°.
Bake for about 45 minutes or until when toothpick is inserted it comes out clean.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake in two 8-inch round pans.
Slice each in half the round way, making four layers.

title: hannah's summercicles
directions: You also need an ice cube tray and popsicle sticks.

title: shepherd pie
directions: Chop onions and saute.
Add ground beef and season to taste. Drain off fat.
Pour cooked ground beef into bottom of an ungreased 13 x 9 baking dish.
Spread frozen corn over top of cooked beef. Spread cooked mashed potatoes over the corn.
Then add cheese to cover top.
Place in a 350° preheated oven.
Cover the pan with tinfoil for the first 20 minutes, then remove foil for 10 more minutes to brown cheese.

title: muffins
directions: Sift flour once; measure and sift again with salt, soda and baking powder. Cut in the shortening; add milk gradually to form soft dough. Turn out on lightly floured board; roll out and cut with biscuit cutter. Bake in hot oven of 450° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chipped beef roll
directions: Shred chipped beef.
Add all ingredients and mix well.
Shape into a ball or log.
Can be rolled in chopped nuts if desired. Chill. Delicious with crackers or Melba toast.

title: carrots
directions: Mix baby carrots and celery.
Put in a casserole dish.
Add a little water to cover.
Add butter and bake in microwave 15 to 20 minutes or until done.

title: jersey chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chicken.
Put in covered baking dish.
Layer chicken on top.
Let stand during the day.
Bake 1 hour, covered, at 350°.
Uncover.
Flip chicken.
Stir around rice and cook 1/2 hour or more, uncovered.

title: avocado-shrimp cocktail
directions: Peel and cube avocado.
Peel and divide the grapefruit into segments; remove seeds.
In a bowl, combine mayonnaise, chili sauce and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Add fruit and shrimp to the mayonnaise mixture.
Toss lightly to combine ingredients.
Spoon into stemmed dishes.
Serve chilled.

title: lazy lasagne
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cook noodles; drain.
Combine sauce, oregano and salt.
Make 2 complete layers with all ingredients. Bake for 30 minutes.

title: arline's fruitcake cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and butter. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour and spices together, then add flour and orange juice alternately.
Mix well. Add fruit and nuts. Chill overnight.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Makes 300 cookies.

title: microwave peanut brittle(10 minutes; easy.)
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a 2-quart glass measure with handle (a must!!).
Cook 8 minutes on High, stirring after first 4 minutes.
Then add butter and vanilla and stir in.
Cook 2 minutes more on High.
Add soda last and quickly stir until blended and foamy.
Immediately pour into 3 well-greased small pie pans (like frozen pie comes in) or onto 1 greased cookie sheet.
Makes one pound.

title: parmesan chicken(serves 4)
directions: You will need a 12-inch nonstick skillet.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill.
This is best made a day ahead.
You can use dried onion flakes.

title: caesar salad
directions: Have all ingredients ready.
In large wooden or glass bowl, smash garlic with spoon and rub all over bowl.
Add salt, mustard and pepper and rub well into garlic.
Add anchovy paste and blend well.
Add vinegar and Worcestershire sauce and blend well.
Add oil and blend well.
Add egg and blend well.
Add lemon juice and blend well.
Add salad greens and toss to coat.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and toss.
Add croutons and toss.
Serve immediately.

title: marinated chicken
directions: Combine ingredients, stirring until well blended.
Pour over chicken.
In a shallow container, cover, and marinate 2 to 3 hours.

title: microwave quiche lorraine
directions: Using a microwave bacon rack, cook bacon on High 6 to 7 minutes or until crisp (or layered between and covered with paper towels on a paper plate).
Crumble bacon. Sprinkle half of the bacon and all the cheese over baked crust and set aside.
Combine salt, nutmeg, pepper and flour in a 4-cup glass measure. Gradually stir in milk until well blended. Stirring twice, cook on High 3 1/2 minutes or until bubbly.
Slowly stir hot mixture into beaten eggs.
Carefully pour into crust.
Sprinkle top with remaining bacon and onions.
Rotating dish once, cook on Medium 10 to 11 minutes. Brown 5 to 6 minutes.
(If your microwave doesn't have a browning feature, place the quiche under the broiler until the top is set and lightly browned.)

title: pork chops (or chicken) and rice
directions: In deep sided cast-iron or ovensafe skillet, melt butter or oil; add celery and onion and cook until tender.
Add chops or chicken and lightly brown.
Add rice, soup and water.
Simmer and add sage.
Cover and bake in 375° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: waldorf red cake
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Make a paste of food coloring and cocoa.
Add paste to creamed mixture and mix. Add buttermilk alternately with salt, flour and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Combine soda and vinegar in a small bowl and add foaming mixture to rest of cake mixture.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch layer cake pans.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil. Add dry ingredients and alternate with eggs.
Add crushed pineapple, carrots, pecans and vanilla. Bake in a well-greased pan at 350°.

title: catfish stew
directions: Dice fatback into small pieces.
Fry until tender; also fry fatback skin until fat is cooked off.
Place in stew pot. Saute onions until tender, not brown, in fatback grease.
Add all to pot.
Fillet and chop onions and potatoes.
Add to pot; simmer until done.
Let skin cook in stew until just before serving.

title: christmas sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Chill in refrigerator. Roll into ball, then in sugar.
Place on cookie sheet; press down with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Decorate with colored sugar.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: creamy caramel pecan rolls
directions: Topping:
Mix sugar and cream.
Divide into 2 round pans and sprinkle some chopped nuts into pans.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs well.
Combine all the dry ingredients.
Add this mixture to the creamed mixture, alternately with the reserved pineapple juice.
Mix well.
Fold in pineapple. Pour into a greased and floured 10 x 13-inch pan.

title: crock-pot french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter until golden.
Stir in flour and sugar. Put mixture in crock-pot and add all remaining ingredients.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.
Put soup in bowls.
Add croutons; top with Mozzarella cheese and put in oven or microwave to melt cheese.

title: old fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream oleo, sugars, egg and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Sift together and add flour, soda, salt and spices.
Beat about 2 minutes longer.
Fold in raisins, chips, walnut meats and oats. Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Makes about 2 dozen cookies.

title: wild rice salad
directions: Marinate at least 1 1/2 hours or overnight.

title: steak bake
directions: Cut steak in about 3 x 3-inch pieces.
Dip in flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in skillet.
Layer in large casserole dish: carrots, steak and celery.
Mix tomato soup with 1 can water. Cover and bake for 2 hours.

title: hawaiian beans
directions: In skillet, cook onion in margarine until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat, stirring now and then.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: In large frying pan over medium heat, saute onion in oil until soft.
In small bowl, combine catsup, sugar, soy sauce, lemon juice and pepper; add to onion.
Add chicken to pan; bring to boil. Cover; simmer for 25 to 35 minutes, or until chicken is done. Remove chicken.
Dissolve cornstarch with 2 tablespoons water; add to pan with sauce.
Cook until it thickens.
Place chicken on cooked rice, then pour sauce over chicken.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt butter; mix other ingredients.
Pour in pan. Refrigerate.

title: double hot horseradish mustard
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender container and process on high until smooth.
Place in small jar and cover tightly; store in refrigerator.
Makes 1/2 cup.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice, then add other ingredients.
Put in graham cracker crust.
Chill for 4 hours.

title: pepsi cola cake
directions: Boil together cocoa, Pepsi and margarine.
Put flour, sugar and salt in mixing bowl and pour hot Pepsi mixture over this. Beat until smooth.
Beat in whole eggs and vanilla.
Stir in by hand the buttermilk and soda.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour on Hot Pepsi Icing.
A very moist cake.

title: snow salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Put in freezer for 6 hours before serving.
Can be refrozen for later time.

title: modernized chicken almond
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add celery and onion.
Stir and cook 2 minutes.
Add chicken and mushrooms.
Heat 8 minutes more.
Combine cornstarch, soy sauce and consomme.
Stir slowly into chicken mixture.
Stir and heat carefully 5 minutes.
Stir in almonds. Serve hot on fluffy rice.

title: blueberry cheese pie
directions: In a large bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Beat in condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Chill 3 hours or until set.
Top with desired amount of pie filling before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Cook roast in crock-pot on high 4 to 5 hours.
Shred meat into bite-size pieces.

title: poke weed casserole(spinach, chard or other greens)
directions: Simmer in water enough young poke weed for 4 people.
Make a white sauce by melting butter in saucepan.
Stir in flour and stirring slowly, add milk.
Season to taste with salt and pepper. Add diced green pepper.
Bring to a simmer.
Spread a base of poke weed over bottom of well greased casserole.
Cover with white sauce, then with sliced egg.
Repeat until all the ingredients are used.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 1/2 hour.

title: greek spinach and cheese turnovers
directions: Phyllo dough:
Carefully unroll as many sheets as needed; store remainder immediately.
Place the sheets not immediately in use between linen tea towels to prevent drying.
If weather is very dry, sprinkle a little water on towels.
Stack 2 leaves together cutting through both strips, cut strips 2 inches wide and 16 inches long.
Brush with melted butter.
Place a teaspoon filling on 1 end of strip.
Fold strip to opposite side, forming a triangle and enclosing filling.
Continue folding as you would an American flag to end of strip.
Brush with melted butter.
Make on ungreased baking sheet at 375° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: italian chicken and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Stir together water, rice, tomatoes, cheese spread, onions and one tsp. Italian seasoning into greased 13 x 9 inch baking dish. Top with chicken; sprinkle with parmesan cheese and remaining Italian seasoning. Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until chicken is tender. Let stand 5 minutes. 4 to 6 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello and hot water to dissolve jello.
Let set until syrupy.
Grind cranberries, apples and bananas together with sugar. Add fruit mixture to syrupy jello.
Then add Cool Whip and pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Place in refrigerator to set.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and let set overnight.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add apples and beat on low.
Add dry ingredients that have been mixed together.
Lastly add nuts and coconut.
Put in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix cooked squash, egg, pepper and onions.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° about 40 minutes.

title: beef fillets with stilton-portobello sauce
directions: Rub fillets with tarragon and pepper. Melt 2 tablespoons butter in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Cook fillets 4 to 5 minutes on each side or to desired degree of doneness. Remove from skillet and keep warm.

title: rice with pork
directions: Cut pork in small pieces and put it in pan.
Add water in pan just enough to cover pork and cook for 30 minutes.
Chop up onions and carrots and fry, stirring for 10 minutes, using butter.
Boil rice for 10 minutes and mix everything with it.
Add tomato sauce. Mix it in and cook on low for 10 more minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook onions and carrots in butter until tender, but not brown. Blend in flour, 1 teaspoon salt and milk.
Add broth all at once. Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Add remaining ingredients in casserole and top with pie crust.
Put in oven and brown pie crust.

title: martha washington balls
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients and chill. Melt the paraffin and chocolate chips together and dip balls.

title: judy's coconut cake
directions: Bake cake layers as directed.
Cool and slice to make 4 layers. Mix sugar and sour cream and blend well.
Add 1 1/2 packages coconut and stir well.
Reserve 1 cup of this mixture for top and sides.
Add drained pineapple.
Do not add to the reserved mixture. Spoon pineapple juice over each layer before icing.
Add the reserved icing to the Cool Whip.
Mix thoroughly and spread over the top and sides.
Sprinkle remaining package of coconut on top and sides.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: old kentucky jam cake
directions: Mix as any cake and bake in layers.
Put together with a favorite chocolate filling.
Put wine on each layer before filling.

title: oatmeal pecan cookies
directions: Mix margarine and sugars together.
Add egg and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add to other ingredients.
Stir in oatmeal, pecans and raisins.
Pour onto wax paper.
Makes about 3 logs.
Chill.
Slice and bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: papa's chow chow
directions: Wash and scald tomatoes.
Peel and cut up.
Shred cabbage and cucumbers; add green tomatoes, cut up.
Put in large dishpan to cook.
Slice or chop peppers in chopper and add to vegetables.
Add other ingredients.
Stir constantly, cooking on medium after bringing to a boil.
Cook 3 to 4 hours, until thick.
Makes 15 to 18 pints.
Seal jars; let cool.

title: mama marone's gravy(add tlc and pasta)
directions: Place olive oil in pot with garlic.
Brown garlic and remove cloves.
Brown pork, braciola and pieces of pepperoni and remove. Add tomato paste and water, letting it simmer until it melts.
Add tomato puree and water, letting it simmer until it bubbles.
Place browned meats in sauce.
Simmer 2 hours.
Add meatballs for an additional hour.
Make your favorite pasta.
Place Mama Marone's Gravy on top of pasta.
You may want to serve the meat separately. Serves 4.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring to rolling boil the first 4 ingredients.
Cook for 1 minute.
Add peanut butter; stir until peanut butter melts.
Remove from heat; add remaining 2 ingredients.
Blend well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto wax paper and let set until cool.

title: spicy chicken wing appetizers
directions: Cut off tips of chicken wings, if desired.
Place wings, soy sauce, sugar, five spices powder, water and garlic powder in a saucepan.
Cover and simmer about 25 minutes or until wings are almost done.
If not using immediately, refrigerate right in the cooking liquid.

title: fruit delight
directions: Drain fruit and cherries and save juice.
In medium pan, put a total of 6 cups liquid (use juice and add water to make 6 cups). Add liquid slowly to vanilla and tapioca pudding mixes.
Add orange extract and cook until thick (boiling point).
Remove from heat and cool (about 1/2 hour).
After cooling, put fruit and sliced bananas into mixture and stir.
Refrigerate.

title: cherry shortbread cookies
directions: Stir together flour, sugar and nutmeg in a mixing bowl.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Mix in cherries and food coloring.
Form mixture into a bowl and knead until smooth.
Shape dough into 1 inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Using the bottom of a glass, slightly flatten balls to 1/2 inch.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until edges are firm and bottoms are lightly browned.
Remove and cool cookies on a wire rack.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook jumbo pasta shells as directed on package.
Combine all ingredients.
Fill each pasta shell with mixture.
Bake at 350°, covered with foil, for 20 minutes and then, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Let set.
Cover with sauce.

title: sweet and fast for lea
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, add sugars and melted butter; mix.
Add remaining ingredients in order, stirring them in one at a time until all mixed.
Spread mixture by patting it down in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Then keep away from Lea, Kristin and Kattie so Dad gets some.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Stir in crushed chips, nuts and flour.
Chill.
Roll dough into balls and press with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a Bundt pan.

title: corn stuffed peppers
directions: Remove tops and insides of peppers.
Wash and drain thoroughly.
Place the peppers upright in a shallow pan.
Add 1/2-inch water to pan.
Mix all the remaining ingredients.
Spoon into peppers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until peppers are tender.

title: meat ball stew
directions: Measure Corn Flakes into large bowl.
Crush slightly.
Stir into egg, 1/4 cup beef broth, salt and pepper.
Beat well and add ground beef.
Mix well.
Make into balls and brown meat balls in oil in frying pan over medium heat.
Pour off excess fat.
Stir in the remaining beef broth, tomato soup, water, thyme, carrots, onion rings and potatoes.
Cover and cook over medium heat about 25 minutes or until meat balls are thoroughly cooked.
Pour into individual bowls.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes.

title: company best pickles(chunk)
directions: Cover whole cucumbers with boiling water; allow to stand until the next morning.
Drain.
Repeat for the next 3 mornings.
On the fifth day, drain and slice in 1/2-inch pieces.
Combine sugar, spice and vinegar; bring to a boil and pour over cucumbers.
Let stand for 2 days.
On the third day, bring to a boil and seal in hot jars.

title: layered enchilada casserole
directions: Coat a nonstick skillet with cooking spray; place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add meat, onions and garlic; cook until browned.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Set aside after simmering for 5 minutes.
Combine cottage cheese and egg white in small bowl.
Stir well.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix crushed pineapple, sugars, and orange juice until well blended.
Add cornstarch for thickening.
After mixing the above together pour into one unbaked pie shell.
Top with second unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or until filling is set and pie crusts are brown.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift all dry ingredients into a large bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk, then yeast.
Stir until thoroughly moistened.
Turn onto floured board and knead a minute or two.
Roll out to desired thickness and cut into rounds. Brush with melted butter and bake on ungreased pan at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes, or lightly browned.
These freeze well.

title: fresh fruit crisp
directions: Combine oats, brown sugar, flour, sugar, cinnamon and salt. Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs; set aside.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Macaroni (cooked and drained); add chopped cucumbers, green peppers, onions, parsley flakes, salt and pepper.
Mix together with mayonnaise.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, salt and celery seed.
Pour over the vegetables and let stand.

title: cheddar crisps
directions: Mix butter and grated cheese until light and fluffy.
Add flour gradually.
Add salt and cayenne pepper and blend well.
Add cereal and blend.
Take 1 teaspoon and roll into a ball.
Place 2 inches apart on baking sheet.
Flatten each with floured fork. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden.
Keep in airtight container 1 week or may be frozen.
Great for hors d'oeuvres.

title: maw maw's no fail divinity candy
directions: Bring the sugar, Karo syrup, water and salt to the soft ball stage and add 1 cup of mixture to 2 beaten egg whites along with the marshmallows.
Cool remainder of egg whites to hard ball stage.
Add remainder to egg whites mixture slowly, then add vanilla and pecans.
Beat slowly until mixture dulls, then spoon drops onto wax paper.

title: quick chicken marengo
directions: Slice chicken breasts and brown in 2 tablespoons hot oil and garlic clove.
Set aside.
Saute onions, peppers and mushrooms until tender and add chicken.
Add tomato sauce and 1/2 cup wine, if desired.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Serve over bed of rice.

title: grandma's turnips
directions: Combine turnips with mashed potatoes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add melted butter.
Fold in cheese just before serving.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix soup and water together; add to rice.
Put rice mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan or Pyrex casserole.
Sprinkle top with onion soup. Place chicken pieces on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Melt butter and mix with remaining ingredients. Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake one hour at 350 degrees or until set and brown.

title: karo sweet 'n sour pork
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
In a large skillet, heat corn oil over medium-high heat. Add next 3 ingredients.
Stir-fry 2 minutes or until tender-crisp.

Remove. Stir-fry pork, half at a time, 3 minutes. Return pork to skillet. In a bowl, stir together pineapple juice and remaining 5 ingredients. Stir into skillet. Add green pepper mixture and pineapple, stirring constantly. Bring to a boil over medium heat and boil 1 minute. If desired, serve over rice.

title: okra fritters
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients, stirring well.
Drop mixture by tablespoons into hot oil.
Cook until golden brown, turning once.

title: pumpkin dump cake
directions: Mix all ingredients (except cake mix, nuts and butter) together in a large bowl.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over top.
Then sprinkle nuts over cake mix.
Pour melted butter over all.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: quick meat balls
directions: Mix seasoning mix with ground chuck.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Bake in 350° oven for about 15 minutes.
Cut wieners in 1-inch pieces.
Combine meat balls, wieners and barbecue sauce.
Serve in slow cooker or in chafing dish.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together and put in 3-quart casserole. Put grated cheese on top.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Stir in carrots, raisins, pecans, coconut and apples.
In a separate bowl, beat eggs with oil and vanilla. Stir into dry ingredients until just combined. Spoon into well buttered (1/3 cup) muffin tins, filling to the top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until springy to the touch.

title: mud pie
directions: Melt butter/margarine in a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Stir in graham crackers and sugar.
Mix well and firmly pat in bottom of pan.
Microwave 5 minutes.

title: rice krispies bars
directions: Heat sugar and syrup to just bubbling.
Add peanut butter and chocolate chips or M&M's and stir.
Add enough Rice Krispies until right consistency (about 4 cups).
Pat down in 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: Put mushrooms in a kettle with 2 cups boiling water, bouillon cubes and onion.
Bring to a boil and simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Melt butter in saucepan and blend in flour.
Gradually add milk and cook, stirring, until slightly thickened.
Add to mushrooms and season to taste with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Makes about 1 1/2 quarts.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease a Bundt pan.
Place rolls evenly in pan.
Pour melted butter over rolls.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Top with nuts and sprinkle pudding over all.
Let thaw on counter overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes the next morning.
Take out of pan immediately and put on rack which is on cookie sheet. The syrup will drip off.
If you wait 3 minutes, you can scoop it up and put on rolls.

title: hot seafood dip
directions: Drain seafood and mix all ingredients together.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20 minutes.
Use to spread on crackers or small breads.
May be doubled.

title: applesauce-oat cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, cream together shortening, brown sugar and granulated sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add applesauce; mix well.
Sift together flour, salt, cinnamon, baking powder and baking soda.
Add dry ingredients to applesauce mixture, mixing well.
Stir in oats and raisins.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 7 dozen cookies.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Blend sugar and oil well.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add pumpkin, sift dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture; beat on low, and add raisins and nuts, if desired.
Grease pans; bake about 1 hour, at 350°.
Makes four 6 x 3 1/2 x 2-inch or two 9 x 5 x 2 3/4-inch loaves.

title: swedish cod chowder
directions: In Dutch oven over medium heat, cook spuds and onion in butter, stirring occasionally, 10 minutes.
Stir in salt, pepper, bay leaf and water.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add milk and fish; bring just to boil.
Reduce heat and cover.
Simmer very gently for 15 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork. Sprinkle with dill weed (optional).

title: cinnamon cheese coffee cake
directions: Unroll and spread 1 package crescent rolls on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread to sides and pinch seams to make a solid covering.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Dissolve jello in water. Defrost berries, chop up half package and set aside for frosting.
Prepare cake mix as directed.
Add 1/2 berries, oil, eggs and jello mixture.
Mix well for 3 minutes. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 300° and bake for 15 to 20 minutes longer or until done.
Frost with powdered sugar mixed with margarine and reserved berries.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread bean dip on large plate or platter.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning.
Spread over bean dip.
Top with cheese, olives and tomatoes, as much or as little as you like.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Bring to a boil the chicken stock, potatoes, onion and Tabasco sauce. Simmer until the potatoes are tender. Add sliced cheese and heat until cheese is melted. Add butter and seasoning.
Puree all of this in blender. Return to double boiler and fold in heavy cream.
Garnish with parsley or a shock of dried dill. Serves 6 to 8.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine egg, milk, 2/3 cup cracker crumbs, 1/4 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Stir in onion, corn and pimiento; mix well. Turn into a 1-quart casserole.
Toss margarine with remaining crumbs; sprinkle atop corn mixture.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until a knife inserted near center comes out clean.

title: wall cleaner(for painted surfaces)
directions: No rinsing necessary.
May be used in a spray bottle.

title: quick corn bread dressing
directions: While corn bread is baking, boil, then bring to simmer the can of soup with one can of water, green onions, bell pepper and celery.
After corn bread has cooled, crumble into bowl.
Pour liquid ingredients over it and chopped eggs.
Stir and season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: layered pea salad
directions: Chop or shred lettuce and spread evenly in a wide 3 to 4-quart bowl or 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Top with a layer each of onions, celery, carrots, water chestnuts and frozen peas.
Frost evenly with mayonnaise.
Sprinkle with cheese, sugar, salt and garlic powder.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Serves 12.

title: breakfast before
directions: Prepare the night before:
In 9 x 13-inch buttered pan, place 6 slices of torn bread; add skinless sausage, cooked and drained. In bowl, beat eggs, milk, Cheddar cheese, onion salt, garlic salt and dry mustard.
Pour this mixture into pan over bread and sausage.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.
Super for company.

title: clam dip
directions: In mixing bowl, combine first 6 ingredients.
Mix well.
Stir in clams, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: pink salad
directions: Boil pineapple and juice.
Add sugar and jello.
Cool.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Chill until firm.

title: vegetable filled omelet
directions: Filling:
Boil in a saucepan the zucchini, mushrooms, green onion and green pepper until vegetables are tender-crisp; drain well.
Add undrained tomatoes, basil, 1/2 teaspoon salt and sugar. Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Combine 1 tablespoon cold water and cornstarch.
Add to tomato mixture; cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Keep filling warm while preparing omelets.

title: cocktail smokies
directions: Cut refrigerated biscuits in half.
Wrap each sausage in a biscuit half.
Put on biscuit pan and cook at 400° until biscuit is brown.

title: jack-o-lantern cheese ball(childrens treat)
directions: Beat cheese, pumpkin, preserves and spices in medium bowl until smooth. Cover and refrigerate 2 or 3 hours, or until cheese is firm enough to shape. Shape into round pumpkin. Place on serving plate. Using knife, score vertical lines down pumpkin. Place pretzel
rod in top for stem. Cut bread into triangles for eyes and black olive slices curved upwards to form smile. Cut red pepper in one triangle for nose and two for ears.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 1/2 cups hot water.
Grind cranberries and orange, using half the rind.
Cover with sugar and let stand 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
When jello begins to jell, add celery, nuts, pineapple and cranberries.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Pour all ingredients, except 1 cup marshmallows, into a 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Add 1 cup marshmallows to top and broil.
Watch carefully.

title: ruby's biscuits
directions: Sift flour, sugar and baking powder together.
Cut shortening into flour mixture.
Mix in buttermilk with a fork until just moistened.
Form a large ball.
Put on a floured surface and knead a few times.
Roll out about 3/4 inch biscuit center.
Place on a greased baking sheet with sides of biscuits touching.
Bake at 450° about 15 minutes, until brown.

title: tex-mex "cheap" salsa
directions: Cook jalapenos in water until soft.
Pour can of tomatoes and jalapenos (without water) in blender.
Add garlic salt to taste. "Ole."
Cheap salsa.
This will last about a week if you refrigerate it properly.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco; add sugar, then add dry ingredients. Add vanilla and milk.
Beat well about 4 minutes.
Bake 2 hours at 325°.

title: beef-spinach stuffed manicotti
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Heat the olive oil in a skillet.
Add beef and onion.
Cook until meat has lost its pinkness.
Put the meat and onion in a bowl and mix with the bread crumbs, cheese, eggs, spinach, salt and pepper.
Stuff the cooked manicotti with the mixture and make a single layer in an 11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 1 3/4 -inch baking dish, allowing space between the manicotti for expansion.
Spoon the tomato sauce on top, cover with foil and bake 45 minutes.

title: sugar cure meat
directions: Mix salt, brown sugar, black pepper, red pepper and salt peter.
Mixture is enough for each joint of meat.

title: turtle brownies
directions: Melt margarine and allow to cool before combining with 1/3 cup evaporated milk and cake mix; mix well.
Place half the batter in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 5 to 8 minutes at 350° until puffy, but not done.
Melt caramels and remaining evaporated milk in saucepan; blend well and set aside.
Sprinkle pecans and chocolate chips over batter in pan; drizzle caramel mixture over top.
Carefully drop and spread remaining batter over top.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Makes 10 servings.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs and margarine together and press into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix confectioners sugar, cream cheese and eggs together and pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool, then cut.

title: mile high strawberry pie
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add a little sugar and a strawberry; continue beating.
Alternate sugar and strawberries, a little at a time.
Continue beating until sugar and strawberries are all gone.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in graham cracker crust. Pile it in until you have used it all and freeze immediately. Freeze about 8 hours before serving.

title: lemon-buttered new potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water to cover for 10 minutes or until tender.
Carefully drain, leaving skins intact.
In a small saucepan, combine butter and rest of ingredients (except parsley). Cook over medium heat until butter melts.
Pour over potatoes. Garnish with fresh parsley.
Serve immediately.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cinnamon mini muffins
directions: Melt butter in boiling water.
Add flour and salt all at once. Beat and cook until mixture forms a ball that doesn't separate. Remove from heat, cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each one.

Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet (or fill a pastry bag with dough and squeeze out onto sheet "cutting" the dough off from the bag with a spatula or knife). Bake at 400° until golden brown and fluffy, about 30 minutes. Remove from oven, split open and remove any soggy centers.
Cool on rack.
Fill.
These may be made ahead and frozen for a few weeks.
Yield: 40 to 50 little ones.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add liquid and mix to a batter that will drop from spoon.
Drop from teaspoon into boiling stew or soup pot, being careful that there is plenty of liquid and no possibility of boiling dry.
Cover tightly and cook, undisturbed, from 10 to 20 minutes, depending on size of dumplings.

title: squash souffle
directions: Boil squash and onion until tender.
Drain off water.
Add egg.
Crumble crackers and add cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Top with cheese.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix and beat with mixer until smooth.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine in a 10-inch pie pan.
Pour filling on top of margarine. Bake 35 minutes in 325° oven.
Makes its own crust.

title: olive-nut sandwich spread
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add other ingredients.
Put in covered container and refrigerate for 24 to 48 hours (mixture will thicken).

title: spaghetti pizza casserole
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle well with Parmesan cheese.
Add cooked spaghetti and mix well with butter and cheese.
Layer all following items.
Cover spaghetti with 12 ounces cheese.
Top with pepperoni and add spaghetti sauce. Finish off with another layer of 12 or more ounces cheese, topped with pepperoni.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until all cheese melts.

title: angel food delight
directions: Let Jell-O stand until partially set and then whip.
Roll cake in Jell-O and then in coconut.
Put in refrigerator to set.

title: baked chicken breasts with dried beef
directions: Cover bottom of 9 x 9-inch pan with dried beef.
Add a cube of Swiss cheese to each chicken breast; roll and wrap each breast with a strip of bacon.
Fasten with toothpicks, if necessary.
Arrange chicken on dried beef.
Mix undiluted soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Bake uncovered at 300° for 3 hours.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: In a skillet, 1 tablespoon hot margarine, cook chicken for 10 minutes or until brown; remove.
In an additional 1 tablespoon hot margarine, cook broccoli and mushrooms until tender and liquid is evaporated.
Stir often and add carrots, if desired.
Add soups and milk, heat to boiling.

title: tea
directions: Boil the water.
Put in tea bags.
Steep 40 to 45 minutes. Put about 2 1/2-inches water in gallon jar. Add sugar and small can lemonade. Finish filling jug with water. Will keep several days without becoming cloudy.

title: little granny's homemade rolls
directions: Combine milk, boiling water, sugar, salt and shortening.
Stir until shortening is melted; cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water; add to milk mixture with eggs, mixing well.
Add 4 cups flour and beat well.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double in bulk, about 1 to 2 hours.

title: grape jelly
directions: Combine juice and sugar and bring to a boil.
Stir constantly. Add bottle of Certo and boil hard for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and take off foam with slotted spoon.
Pour into jars (small baby food jars are good).
Makes 18 jars.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix together and store in large plastic container.
Use 4 or 5 heaping teaspoons into hot water.

title: wonderful dill sweet pickles
directions: Drain dill juice off.
Pour in large bowl.
Pour sugar over pickles and stir until sugar melts.
Stir each day for 3 days. Put back in gallon jar.

title: icebox fruit cake(serves 8)
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Pour in can of Eagle Brand milk slowly and mix with hands.
Add 1/2 of the cherry juice. Pour into jello-ring to mold.
Store in refrigerator at least overnight.
Unmold on serving plate and slice thin to serve.
May also be put in loaf pan.

title: bisquick mix
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt; cut in Crisco with pastry blender.
Store in container at room temperature.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Break up sausage in frying pan.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes (do not brown).
Pour boiling water over cornmeal; put in drained sausage. Beat eggs; add milk and salt.
Combine with sausage mixture.
Add shortening and baking powder.
Stir well.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole; bake at 375° for one hour.
Serves 8.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients real well.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until brown.
Makes 150 to 190.

title: dark fruit cake
directions: Boil first 5 ingredients for 3 minutes.
Cool.
Add to dry ingredients.
Fold in cherries and nuts.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325° in a large greased tube pan.

title: white corn salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine oil, vinegar, brown sugar, salt and pepper; mix well. Add corn, tomato, onion and bell pepper; toss to combine.
Cover and refrigerate until serving time. Serves 8.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all together with corn bread.
Bake 30 minutes or until brown.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly together.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Makes 3 pies.

title: three bean bake
directions: Fry onions and garlic until tender.
Mix other ingredients. Then add garlic and onions.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: ambrosia
directions: Combine fruit and juice.
Chill.
Arrange fruit on bed of lettuce leaves.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: chicken barbecue
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken and simmer for 10 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Put chicken in 9 x 13 pan.
Pour sauce over and marinate several hours in refrigerator.
Bake in oven at 350° until done or can be grilled on pit.

title: hershey bar pound cake
directions: Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs.
Blend in flour mixture. Add buttermilk, syrup and melted candy bars.
Beat well. Bake at 350°.
Check in 45 minutes because cake can burn easily. Be sure to greased and flour cake pan.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, vanilla, peanut butter and milk in casserole.
Do not stir.
Slice margarine across top of these ingredients.
Cook on High (covered) for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove and stir well.
Pour into buttered pan (about 8 or 9-inch round or square).
Refrigerate until cool and set.

title: fruit cake
directions: Stew raisins in 1 cup water for 15 minutes.
Put baking soda in 1 cup cold water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased bread pans.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: easy caramel popcorn
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Place popped corn in large roasting pan.
Let stand in oven while preparing glaze.

title: slush punch
directions: Bring 4 cups water to a boil and stir in the sugar and Jell-O until all is dissolved.
Divide mixture between 2 one gallon jugs. Divide the 8 ounces of lemon juice in half and pour into jugs. Add 1 can pineapple juice to each gallon.
Add the remaining 10 cups of water, 5 into each jug.
Freeze.
Take out of freezer 4 to 5 hours before serving.
Shake and stir well.

title: seasoning salt
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Cover and blend on high speed for 20 seconds.
Store tightly in covered container.
Use as needed.

title: creamy lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium mixing bowl, beat egg yolks; stir in sweetened condensed milk, lemon juice and food coloring. Pour into crust; bake 8 minutes.
Make up meringue and spread over pie.
Return to oven just until meringue begins to brown.
Cool. Chill thoroughly and keep refrigerated.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Mix all well; put in a casserole dish.
Mix 2 cups of Bisquick and water to make pastry mixture.
Drop on top.
Cover.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes; cool and serve with ice cream.

title: summer-style tuna-fishin' salad
directions: Rinse tuna thoroughly after opening can, and put into medium size mixing bowl.
Shred with a fork.
Add remaining ingredients without lettuce leaves.
Mix thoroughly.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Brown and drain ground meat; chop up cheese.
Put in crock-pot with Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Put in meat and mix up, then enjoy.

title: better than sex
directions: Mix cake following instructions on box.
Add coconut and vanilla.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool completely.
Punch holes in cake with toothpicks.
Cook together for 10 minutes the pineapple and sugar.
Cool and then spread over baked cake.
Mix together pudding mix and milk.
Beat until thick.
Spread over cake.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix cherry pie mix and pineapple in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix on top.
Add coconut and pecans for top.
Pour melted butter over all.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: orangey carrot and raisin salad
directions: Blend drink mix into mayonnaise.
Combine carrots, raisins and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Chill 1 hour and stir before serving.

title: potato soup
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Boil covered until tender.
Use as little water as possible.
Drain liquid; leave about 1 1/2 inches in bottom of pan.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Wash the roast in cold water.
Mix the salt and pepper in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Roll the roast in the salt and pepper in pan. When all sides of roast are covered with salt and pepper wrap the roast tightly in heavy-duty foil, then wrap it again in white meat wrap paper.
Lay it in the 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 200° for 12 hours.
Serve meat on bun and add your favorite barbecue sauce.

title: easy pound cake(club member: john waters)
directions: Cream butter; beat until smooth. Gradually add sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in lemon extract. Add flour to creamed mixture, beating well until smooth. Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 275°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Steam squash until almost done, then place in large mixing bowl.
Add all other ingredients, except cheese.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into 9 x 13-inch casserole (sprayed with Pam).
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until set.
Top with grated cheese and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: tuna puff
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add celery and onion.
Cook over low heat about 5 minutes.
Do not brown.
Stir in flour.
Add milk (all at once).
Cook, stirring until thick and boiling.
Remove from heat and stir in tuna and salt.
Quickly add egg yolks.
Fold in egg whites.
Turn into greased 9-inch pie pan.
