Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes, until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve hot.

title: raisin oatmeal crispies
directions: Blend butter and sugar, then add oats.
Sift dry ingredients. Add dry ingredients to oats.
Stir in raisins and milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Roll into balls.
Place 3-inches apart on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 4 dozen.

title: chocolate chip freeze
directions: Dip cookies one at a time in milk.
Layer a Pyrex dish, any size, with cookies, layer of Cool Whip.
You'll have 2 layers of each.
Cover with foil and freeze.
Take out 1 hour before serving.

title: easy prune cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil; add eggs and mix.
Sift flour and spices. Add to mixture.
Add prunes.
Drop in nuts and mix.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: stromboli
directions: Roll out pizza dough.
Pinch sides together to make 1 long dough.
Put meat of your choice in first (put in middle). Sprinkle cheese over meat.
Add veggies.
Season to taste.
Roll longways and curve it into a semi-circle.
Brush a beaten egg over the top.
Put on big cookie sheet.
Do not use Pyrex.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes, until golden brown.

title: apricot jam squares
directions: Cream butter or margarine with 3/4 cup sugar and lemon rind until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Spread batter in 12 x 8-inch baking pan.
Cover batter with jam.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but still moist. Add 1/4 cup sugar, beating until meringue forms stiff peaks.
Fold in nuts.
Spread on apricot jam layer.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm.
Cut into squares and cool.
Makes 48 (2-inch) squares.

title: pork and mushroom gravy
directions: Brown sliced pork with garlic.
Remove garlic and drain oil. Add soup and 1 cup water.
Add corn and seasonings.
Simmer about 1/2 hour.
May add more seasoning to your taste.
Serve over rice. Children love this and it's simple and easy, great for working moms.

title: square dance cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and add butter and milk.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add egg whites, vanilla and lemon and beat 2 minutes. Blend in chopped walnuts.
Pour into well-greased and lightly floured 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool and cut cake into 4 squares.
Frost with Checkerboard Frosting.

title: poultry seasoning blend
directions: Mix well and put in spice shaker.
Sprinkle on poultry as desired.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Fry onion in 1/2 stick butter until golden brown.
Add tomato pulp and chili.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Add cheese and cook until melted and smooth.
Use as dip for crackers, Fritos or potato chips.

title: zucchini and mushrooms
directions: Cut zucchini lengthwise into halves.
Cut each half diagonally into 1/4-inch slices.
Cut mushrooms into 1/2-inch slices.
Mix cornstarch and water.
Heat wok or electric skillet until 1 or 2 drops of water bubble and skitter.
When sprinkled in wok, add vegetable oil; rotate wok to coat side.
Add onion and garlic; stir-fry until garlic is light brown.
Add zucchini, mushrooms and salt; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Stir in chicken and soy sauce.
Heat to boiling; stir in cornstarch mixture.
Cook and stir until thickened, about 10 seconds.
Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli cauliflower salad
directions: Break cauliflower and broccoli into small pieces and combine with crumbled bacon, cheese and onion.
Add sauce and marinate at least 4 hours.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Combine in small mixing bowl until blended.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; pour in crushed pineapple with juice and the blueberry pie filling.
Pour into large bowl and let set in freezer until jelled.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and nuts (if desired).
After first part is jelled, put this on top and it is ready to serve.

title: confetti potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water to cover 30 minutes or until tender.
Drain and cool slightly.
Peel and dice potatoes. Combine potatoes, onions, peppers, celery, carrots, olives and eggs in a large bowl.
Combine dressing, sour cream and lemon juice.
Stir well.
Add dressing to vegetable mixture, tossing gently.
Serve on lettuce leaves, if desired, and sprinkle with paprika.
Yields 5 to 6 servings.

title: brownie cupcakes
directions: Combine
chocolate
and
margarine
in a heavy saucepan; cook over
low
heat, stirring constantly, until melted.
Cool mixture slightly.
Combine sugar, flour, eggs and flavorings in a
large mixing
bowl.
Add
chocolate mixture, stirring until batter is smooth.
Stir in
pecans.
Spoon
batter
into paper lined muffin pans, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 325° for about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: baked scallops green lake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Rinse scallops, removing any sand, as well as removing the sweet meat.
Drain on paper towel.
Place scallops in baking dish, one layer thick.
Nearly cover scallops with the cream.
Cut butter in chunks over cream and cover with a thin layer of bread crumbs.
Place in oven and bake until center bubbles (20 to 30 minutes).
Remove and let stand for a few minutes.
If it is too juicy, stir.

title: green punch
directions: Mix
first
ingredients and chill.
Chill ginger ale and add
to Kool-Aid mixture when served.
Makes two gallons. Add 1/2 gallon lime sherbet per gallon punch if desired.

title: indoor s'mores
directions: Butter 9 x 9 x 2-inch square pan.
Heat corn syrup and butter to boiling in 3-quart saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate chips and vanilla; stir until chocolate is melted.
Fold in cereal, 1 cup at a time, stirring gently until completely cooked. Fold in marshmallows.
Press mixture evenly in pan with buttered back of spoon.
Let stand until firm, at least 1 hour.
Cut into bars, about 2 1/4 x 1 1/2-inches.
Makes 24 bars.

title: gourmet sirloin tips
directions: Saute garlic in hot oil over medium heat for 30 seconds.
Add meat and quickly brown meat for about one minute.
Remove from heat.
Mix remaining ingredients in a casserole dish.
Add meat to casserole and stir together.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for one hour or until tender.
Serve over egg noodles or rice.
Makes 4 small servings or 2 large.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: Grate potatoes.
Mix 1 large egg (or 2 small) and onions. Cook in 1 stick (or less) of margarine until glassy.
Then mix potatoes, sour cream, chicken soup, cheese, and salt and pepper. Pour in 9 x 13 baking dish.
Melt 1/2-3/4 stick margarine and mix with crushed cornflakes.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: old-time cookies
directions: Mix all together; chill.
Roll 1/4-inch thick.
Use a 4-inch cookie cutter or make balls and flatten with fork.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° for 9 minutes.
Yields 2 dozen large cookies.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place cooked chicken in 9 x 13 baking dish.
Mix chicken soup with 1/2 can broth, then pour over chicken.
Spread Veg-All over chicken and soup.
Mix buttermilk, flour and butter.
Pour over chicken and Veg-All.
Pour 2 cups chicken broth over top of flour mixture and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger; add to rest of the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate skillet pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add to melted butter in skillet. Beat eggs.
Add milk and vanilla.
Add to skillet.
Cook until thick; stir constantly.

title: forest cake
directions: Mix cake as on package in 3 layers, then cool.
After cake cools, mix marshmallow cream and Cool Whip together.
(May have to use hands to get lumps out.)
Put mix on outside of cake and cherry pie filling in center.
Layer cake like this.
Cover top and side with cream and Cool Whip.
Put 1 cherry on top in center. Grate Hershey bars and sprinkle top and sides.
(Keep in refrigerator.)

title: pumpernickel bread dip
directions: Hollow out large round loaf of pumpernickel bread.
Cut bread removed into large chunks.
Fill hollowed bread shell with dip. There's enough dip for an additional package of pumpernickel rolls.

title: rosy pineapple chicken
directions: Rub chicken pieces with salt, rosemary and pepper.
Arrange in shallow glass baking dish.
Place larger pieces in corners with smaller pieces in center.
Sprinkle shallots over top.
Combine crushed pineapple with juice, paprika, and ginger in small bowl; spoon over chicken.

title: pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Prepare pastry.
Beat eggs, sugar, salt, butter and syrup with rotary beater.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into pastry-lined pan.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Blend in large mixing bowl, oil and eggs.
Beat well.
Add cake mix, lemon pudding, water and lemon flavoring.

title: miracle rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water, set aside.
Mix flour, sugar and soda, cut in Crisco.
Add milk and yeast.
Can be made out immediately or store in refrigerator for 2-3 days.

title: hearty soup with steak and veggies
directions: In a large saucepan, cook beef and onions in oil until meat is no longer pink. Stir in potatoes, carrots and peas. Add the broth, water, vinegar, parsley, chives, basil, thyme, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 35 to 40 minutes.

title: asparagus roll-ups
directions: Cut crusts off bread.
Roll with a rolling pin until bread is flat.
Spread with cheese.
Roll asparagus in bread.
Dip in melted butter.
Freeze.
After they are frozen, cut into thirds. Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.

title: celery salad
directions: Mix jello according to directions. Blend in mayonnaise.
Add other ingredients and chill in a covered dish.

title: cinnamon-crusted baked apples
directions: Coat an 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish with cooking spray; pour water into dish. Peel, core and slice apples.
Arrange apple slices in prepared dish; coat apple slices lightly with vegetable cooking spray.
Combine brown sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg; cut in margarine with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal (I use a fork).
Sprinkle mixture evenly over apples. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until apple is tender. Contains, 2.3 grams of fat per serving.

title: caramel frosting
directions: In medium saucepan, combine sugars, syrup and cream.
Cook over medium heat; stir constantly until mixture comes to boiling, boil without stirring until 236° on candy thermometer or until soft ball stage when dropped into cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, but don't stir.
Cool to 110° or bottom of pan is lukewarm.
Add vanilla.
Beat with wooden spoon until frosting is creamy and barely holds its shape.
Set frosting pan in pan of hot water to keep from hardening before all used.

title: rose petal tea
directions: Preheat oven to 200°.
Place rose petals on an ungreased baking sheet.
Leaving oven door slightly open, dry petals in oven for 3 to 4 hours, or until completely dry, stirring occasionally. In a blender or food processor, finely grind rose petals and tea leaves.
Store in airtight container.
To brew: place 1 teaspoon tea for each 8 ounces of water in a warm teapot.
Bring to a rolling boil and pour over tea.
Steep for 5 minutes, stir and strain.
Serve hot or chilled.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Grease and flour lightly a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together mayonnaise, then add dry ingredients alternately with water until blended.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 365° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Frost with favorite frosting.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown hamburger and onion, then drain.
Fry bacon crisp and crumble.
Put meat mixture in crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients and cook on low for 4 hours.

title: favorite banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine first 6 ingredients.
Beat well; then add baking soda and baking powder. Gently blend in flour.
Stir 20 seconds or until moistened.
Pour into a loaf pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake for 45 minutes, until a toothpick inserted near the middle comes out clean.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and press out excess water.
Mix spinach with remaining ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least 24 hours. Serve with chips or raw vegetables.

title: smoked salmon ball
directions: Remove skin, bones and liquid from salmon.
Drain well.
Mix all ingredients together very well.
Chill four hours.
Roll into one or two balls.
Roll the balls into chopped pecans to cover. Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: pretzel dip
directions: Blend, chill and use with pretzel rods.

title: barbecue
directions: Fry hamburger in lard.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix bread, eggs, mayonnaise and seasonings.
Add crab and mix gently to hold lumps.
If it's too dry, add mayonnaise.
Form into 6 to 8 cakes.
Fry until brown and done.

title: christmas cutout cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking soda, sugar, butter and oleo into crumbs like pie dough and wet it with sour cream.
Put in refrigerator overnight.

title: spinach-artichoke casserole
directions: Drain spinach well, pressing between layers of paper towels. Stir together spinach and next 7 ingredients.
Melt butter in a skillet over medium-high heat.
Add mushrooms and next 3 ingredients; saute 5 minutes.
Stir mushroom mixture and 1 cup cheese into spinach mixture; spoon into a lightly greased 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining 1 cup cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.
tags: shredded Monterey Jack cheese with peppers

title: m&m cookies
directions: Blend in Crisco and sugar; beat in vanilla, water and eggs. Sift remaining dry ingredients together.
Add to sugar and egg mixture.
Mix well and stir in M&M's.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheet; bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
For additional color, press extra M&M's into cookies before baking. Some candies crack.

title: snowmobilers stew
directions: In Dutch oven place half meat, potato and carrots.
Repeat layers.
Add water and tomato sauce.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over top.
Do not stir.
Cover and bake at 250° for 5 hours.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli, celery, purple onion, sunflower seeds, raisins and crumbled bacon together.
Before serving, mix mayo, sugar and vinegar.
Add to salad and serve.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° until done.

title: favorite ratatouille
directions: Saute onion and garlic in 1/3 cup oil.
Add olives through tomatoes to frying pan and stir.
Rinse and dice eggplant and stir into preceding.
Sprinkle with a little olive oil, oregano and basil.
Top with your favorite cheese and bake in large casserole, 45 to 50 minutes at 325°.

title: supper casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese tarts
directions: Cut cream cheese, butter and flour in like for pie. Knead together. Separate into three batches. Roll out and chop into squares. Put Solo filling in center (about 1 teaspoon). Draw up two corners and pinch together. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Use any fillings such as apricot, prune, cherry, pineapple, etc.

title: orange bread
directions: Wash and peel oranges.
Using just the orange part, grind finely and place in double boiler with the sugar and water.
Cook until thick like jam.
Stir constantly.
Cool.
Stir in egg that has been beaten and the milk.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix and put in bread pans.
Makes 1 or 2 loaves, depending on size of pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done in middle using toothpick testing method.

title: jello cake
directions: Mix jello and hot water; let set up very slowly.
Combine cold milk and confectioners sugar.
After the jello sets up, beat the jello and sugar mixture until stiff.

title: chicken breasts diane
directions: Pound chicken breasts slightly with mallet.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Heat 1 tablespoon each of oil and butter in large skillet.
Cook chicken over high heat for 4 minutes on each side.
Transfer to warm serving platter.

title: hawaii chicken breasts
directions: Chop onion using only 1 inch of green tops. Saute in 1 tbsp of butter until glazed. Transfer to crockpot. Coat chicken breasts in seasoned flour. Saute in butter till brown on both sides. Transfer to crock pot. Drain pineapple. Pour juice over chicken, cover and cook on low 3 to 4 hours (high 1 1/2 to 2 hours)
or until breasts are tender. Saute pineapple slices in butter until golden. Place on heated platter. Top
with a chicken breast. Slice avocado into lengthwise strips. Place 2 strips on a chicken breast. Serve pan drippings over rice. Yummy.

title: dilly cheese cubes
directions: Remove crust from bread.
Cut bread into 1-inch cubes; set aside.

title: pepper relish
directions: Pour boiling water over the first 3 ingredients and let stand 5 minutes. Drain all hot water off.
Put into kettle with the remaining ingredients.
Boil for 20 minutes.
Pour in pint jars and seal.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Combine butter and cocoa in a medium saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until butter melts.
Remove from heat; transfer to a large mixing bowl.
Add sugar and eggs; beat at medium speed with an electric mixer until blended.
Add flour, salt, and vanilla; beat until blended.
Stir in pecans.
Spoon batter into a lightly greased 13x9 pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes.
Remove from oven, and sprinkle marshmallows on cake.
Cool in bake on a wire rack.
Cut into squares to serve.
(Chill before slicing for neater squares.)

title: belva lee's chicken casserole
directions: Stir together.
Must be wet.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Top with 1 can of cream of chicken soup while still hot from oven.

title: cheese vegetable soup
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients, cover and let boil.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.

title: swedish pan cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, vanilla, soda, eggs and pineapple (with juice) together.
Stir for 3 minutes.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost with mixture of oleo, cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Add nuts to mixture and spread on cake.
Let stand to ripen.
This cake is best if it's baked in the morning when needed for supper or the night before if needed for lunch.

title: apple crisp
directions: Spread sliced apples in 8-inch square pan (if apples are tart, sprinkle sugar on them).
Sprinkle with mixture of water, cinnamon and salt.
Using pastry blender, work together until crumbly the sugar, flour and butter.
Spread the crumbs evenly over apples. Bake uncovered in 300° oven about 40 minutes, making sure the juice bubbles up over the topping, making it crunchy and delicious.

title: apricot liqueur
directions: In a large jar, combine all ingredients.
Cover and let stand 6 weeks, stirring every 2 weeks.
Remove apricots.
Strain liqueur several times through double thickness of cheesecloth.
Pour into decanter or bottle and cap.
Save the liqueur-soaked apricots for dipping in chocolate!

title: pickled okra
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, heat water, vinegar, sugar, cloves, salt, cumin seed, celery seed and red pepper to boiling.
Add okra; boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool to room temperature. Transfer okra and pickling liquid to jar or container; seal. Refrigerate several hours or overnight before serving.
This will keep up to 2 weeks refrigerated.

title: spiced apple cider
directions: Place spices in cooking pouch.
Bring cider, spices and sugar to a boil. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Float orange slices to garnish.
Makes 25 servings.

title: chocolate chunk cookies
directions: Place chocolate chips, margarine and marshmallows in large microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave on High 2 minutes or until all ingredients are melted.
Place remaining ingredients in large bowl; mix well.
Pour melted mixture over dry mixture.
Stir until well coated.
Drop by tablespoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Refrigerate until firm.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Put salt over cabbage.
Let stand one hour.
Pour off juice. Mix water, sugar and vinegar; let it come to a boil.
Pour this mixture over cabbage and let it cool, then freeze in small containers.

title: fruit slush punch
directions: Mix thoroughly and freeze.
When ready to serve, stir to mash. Add soda pop.
Yields 25 servings.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix everything together and spread in greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: seasoned oyster crackers
directions: Place crackers in large bowl.
In a separate bowl, combine oil, dressing mix and spices.
Pour over crackers.
Stir well. Let dry 30 minutes, stirring every 5 to 8 minutes.
Store in airtight container.

title: cocoa mix
directions: To serve, combine 1/3 cup dry mix and 1 cup hot water.
Top each serving with marshmallows and use peppermint or cinnamon stick as a stirrer.
Makes approximately 4 quarts or enough for 48 servings.
One cup cocoa and more powdered sugar may be added, if desired.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook the macaroni for 4 to 5 minutes.
Use a colander to get rid of the water once the macaroni is cooked.
Melt the butter in a saucepan and mix in the tomato(es), onion (diced) and salt and seasoning (to taste).
Let these ingredients simmer for a couple of minutes.
Add the macaroni and blend everything together.
Simmer for a couple of minutes.
Add the cheese and stir.
Ready to serve.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Grease 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Fill it 3/4 full of apples. Combine cinnamon and 2 to 4 tablespoons sugar.
Sprinkle over apples.

title: popcorn cake for the kids
directions: Melt oleo and marshmallows together; add oil and stir in popped corn, peanuts and gumdrops.
Pack firmly in tube pan.
Let stand 1 hour, then turn out and slice.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal quick bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together in a large bowl.
Stir wet ingredients together then add dry ingredients just until evenly moistened (batter will be lumpy).
Scrape into a buttered and floured 9 x 5 inch loaf pan.

title: sombrero dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: venison steak and gravy
directions: Melt margarine in cast-iron frying pan after thawing steak in cold water for 2 hours. Put steak in hot margarine; turn heat to moderate temperature. Cover lightly with seasonings. Cover and simmer until tender; turn 2 or 3 times. Increase heat and brown on one side. Pour about 3/4 cup water into pan to make gravy.

title: dilled creamed eggs
directions: Blend mushroom soup, chicken soup and milk in saucepan. Combine cornstarch and water.
Add to soup mixture.
Bring to boiling and cook 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in mushrooms, eggs and dill weed.
Heat through.
Just before serving, stir in Sauterne.
Heat, but do not boil.
Serve over toasted English muffins.
Garnish with parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine milk, soup and pepper.
Pour over beans and add 1/2 can onions.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Garnish remaining onions and pimentos.
Bake 5 minutes more.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Cover large cookie sheet with foil.
Separate dough and lay out on cookie sheet.
Bake according to directions, about 10 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and salad dressing mix. Spread over dough after it has cooked.
Pat vegetables into cream cheese mixture.
Spread grated cheese on top.

title: hearty chicken bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix potatoes, half of cheese and 1/2 of onion.
Spoon into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Spread across bottom and up sides to form a shell.
In a bowl, combine chicken, vegetables, soup, milk and seasonings.
Pour into potato shell and bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onion; bake until golden brown.

title: chocolate chip cookies(neiman marcus recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix vegetables together and sliced onion and add to mixture. Add cheese and mayonnaise.
Pour into casserole dish.
Crush 1 roll of Ritz crackers.
Mix with 1 stick margarine.
Spread on top of casserole.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: okra and tomatoes
directions: Wash okra well; cut off tips and stem ends.
Cut okra into 1/2-inch slices.
Combine okra, water, onion, vinegar and 1 teaspoon salt.
Cover and cook over medium-high heat for 15 minutes.
Drain off liquid; cook over low heat until all moisture evaporates.
Add remaining ingredients; cook over medium heat, turning frequently, until brown.

title: pie dough #1
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Mix, shape and roll.
Place in pie pan and bake at 325° to 350° for 5 to 10 minutes, depending on how done you want it.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Combine peanut butter, butter and 1 cup powdered sugar until blended.
Stir in cereal.
Mix remaining 1 cup sugar with enough hot water to make a frosting.
Roll cookies into balls; dip in frosting and roll in chocolate chips.
Let stand until set.

title: strawberry pie
directions: In top of double boiler, combine sugar, cornstarch and butter. Cook until clear.
Remove from heat.
Add few drops red food coloring.
Add strawberry Jell-O.
Stir.
Place whole strawberries in pie crust.
Pour mixture over berries.
Chill several hours. Serve with whipping cream.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Salt chicken on both sides.
Roll chicken in corn flakes and place in baking pan (may line with foil or spray with Pam).
Bake in 350° oven about 1 hour or until tender.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Chop onions and beef.
Save 1 jar of beef to roll ball in. Mix all ingredients together.
Make ball and roll it in chopped beef.
Wrap and chill.
Serve with all types of crackers.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Boil margarine, water and onion in large saucepan.
Add broccoli.
Return to low boil and cook for 3 minutes.
Add 1 1/2 cups rice.
Remove from heat, cover and let stand for 5 to 7 minutes, until rice is fluffy.
Stir in cream of chicken soup and Cheez Whiz.
Return to low heat, if needed, to melt cheese.
Stir in chicken and heat until ready to serve.
Or, at this point, place in casserole dish, top with bread crumbs and cook at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken bits
directions: Soak chicken pieces in an egg mixture (1 egg and milk) for 1 hour. Roll chicken pieces in bread crumbs.
Brown in butter or canola oil.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix well and pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake in 400° oven for approximately 30 minutes.
While baking make topping.

title: zucchini frittata
directions: Beat eggs with salt and pepper in a medium bowl. Beat in Parmesan cheese.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter with oil in a heavy 8 or 10-inch skillet. When butter foams, add onion.
Saute over medium-low heat about 1 minute.
Add zucchini, parsley and garlic.
Saute 3 to 4 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove zucchini mixture with a slotted spoon.
Stir into egg mixture.

title: fruit roll candy
directions: Place sugar, milk, syrup and butter in heavy pan.
Cook until reaches 236° (soft ball stage).
Add dates and mix well until mixture leaves sides of pan.
Mixture will be thickened and dates cooked apart.
Add coconut and walnuts.
Mix well.

title: mi amigo dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium bowl.
Serve warm or chilled with tortilla chips or fresh vegetables.

title: terry's carrot cake
directions: Mix ingredients together until creamy.
Top with chopped walnuts, if desired.

title: three cheese chicken bake
directions: Cook and drain the noodles.
To make the sauce, melt the butter or margarine and cook the onions and green pepper for 2 minutes.
Add the soup, milk, drained mushrooms, basil and pimento.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan and layer in this order: 1/2 of the noodles, 1/2 of the cottage cheese, 1/2 of the chicken, 1/2 of the American cheese, 1/2 of the Parmesan cheese and 1/2 of the sauce.
Repeat.
Save a little of the Parmesan cheese to sprinkle over the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes uncovered.
Let set for 10 minutes before serving.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients all together. Sift together the salt, flour, ginger, cinnamon and cloves. Add to mixture with the water and soda mixture.
Mix well.
Last, add the eggs. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan at 325° for 30 minutes. Serve warm with applesauce or whipped cream.

title: black olive garlic dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and butter. Add olives and onion. Add about 2 tablespoons garlic powder and 1 teaspoon salt to taste. Chill overnight. Serve with garlic chips or crackers.

title: spaghetti sauce with meat
directions: Pour all tomato products in heavy-duty sauce pot.
Add water, spices, spatini and cheese.
Cook on low heat, covered.
Cook ground beef in frying pan constantly stirring until meat is broken into crumbs and is brown.
Pour meat into colander and drain grease off.
Using same frying pan, add 1/2 tablespoon oil, chopped onions and green peppers, diced.
Cook until vegetables are soft but not soggy.
Pour into colander with meat and let drain.
Add meat and vegetables to sauce and cook on low heat four hours, covered, occasionally stirring and adding water when necessary.
Serves 8.

title: dreamy lemon cookies(low-fat, low cholesterol)
directions: Combine cake mix, Cool Whip and egg.
Mix until all ingredients are moist.
Using 2 teaspoons, drop dough into bowl of powdered sugar.
(Make cookies about the size of large marbles.) Place powdered dough on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Drain whole kernel corn.
Butter inside baking dish.
Add egg, flour, sugar and milk and beat together, then add cream-style and whole kernel corn.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: orange barbecue ribs
directions: Place washed and cleaned ribs on rack of a broiler pan.
Brush with barbecue sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, turning and brushing with sauce every 15 minutes.
Place ribs, bone side down; top with orange slices.
Brush with barbecue sauce.
Continue baking 15 minutes or until done.
Serves 6 to 8 people.
This recipe works wonders with chicken also.

title: bell jim date cake
directions: Combine water and soda. Pour over dates. Stir good and cool. Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, beating after each addition. Add dates. Then add flour, allspice, vanilla and pecans. Bake in 3 layers in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pork loin and cabbage kraut
directions: Bake pork loin 45 minutes at 350°.
Cut slit in center top of loin just enough for kraut to seep into.
Put whole can on top. Bake 15 minutes.
Serve.

title: holiday cheese spread
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Add 1 cup walnuts.
If necessary, chill, then form into a ball.
Spread 1/4 cup walnuts on wax paper.
Roll cheese ball in nuts to coat evenly.

title: tuna broccoli soup
directions: In Dutch oven, saute broccoli, onion and garlic in 2 tablespoons butter until broccoli is crisp-tender.
Remove sauted vegetables to a bowl and cover.
Melt remaining butter in Dutch oven.
Stir in flour and basil until well blended.
Cook over low heat for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add hot milk and broth, all at once.
Beat with wire whisk to combine.
Stir over heat until mixture thickens.
Add mushrooms and simmer 15 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in tuna and vegetables.
Garnish with nutmeg and broccoli florets.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes (skin on) until tender, but firm.
Cool.
Slice 1/2-inch thick; add green beans, wedged tomatoes and sliced onion. Season with salt, pepper, oregano, olive oil and vinegar to taste; toss.
Garnish with quartered eggs (lengthwise).

title: chocolate peanut butter shake
directions: Those are silver, these are gold

title: pie crust
directions: Mix ingredients together with fork.
Roll out between 2 pieces wax paper.
Makes 2 (9-inch) crusts.
For one double or 2 single crust pies.

title: easy strudel
directions: Cut margarine into flour as for pie crust.
Add egg yolks, vinegar and water and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight (or at least 3 hours).
Divide dough into 3 parts and work with one at a time.
Roll out on floured cloth to fit 10 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch cookie sheet.
Sprinkle each with 1 tablespoon flour, 3 tablespoons sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Arrange 3 peeled and diced apples along edge of long side and roll up, guiding with the cloth grasped in each hand.
Place on ungreased pan and bake in moderate oven (375°) for 45 minutes.
Serve sprinkled with confectioners sugar.
Makes 3 strudels.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes; peel and dice into small chunks.
Place potatoes, Swiss cheese, green olives and onion in large bowl. Mix.
Add just enough mayonnaise to moisten.
Pour ingredients into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cook at 350° uncovered for about 30 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serves about 10 adults.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; refrigerate.

title: apricot chicken(diabetic)
directions: Combine jelly, soup mix and dressing.
Pour over chicken and marinate for 24 hours.
Bake uncovered for 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Makes 8 servings.

title: pfeffernuesse
directions: Combine flour, sugar, soda, spices and pepper.
In a saucepan, combine molasses and butter.
Heat and stir until butter melts. Cool to room temperature.
Stir in eggs.
Add dry ingredients to molasses mixture.
Mix well.
Cover and chill several hours or overnight.
Grease a cookie sheet.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls. Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 14 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Makes about 60.

title: low-fat chicken marsala
directions: Pat chicken dry and season with salt and pepper.
In large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat, melt 1 1/2 tablespoons margarine.
Add chicken; cook 1 1/2 minutes on each side or until lightly browned.
Stir in broth and Marsala; reduce heat to medium-low and simmer about 2 minutes or until chicken is cooked through.
Remove chicken to warm serving platter.
Increase heat to high and bring pan juices to boil; boil until reduced to about 1/2 cup.
Remove from heat; swirl in remaining margarine until well blended.
Pour sauce over chicken and garnish with lemon slices and parsley.
170 calories; 4 g. fat; 66 mg.
cholesterol; 194 mg. sodium.

title: sweet milk waffles
directions: Separate eggs and beat egg whites until stiff and fold in last.

title: lite rice pudding
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, add cold water to rice (enough to cover).
Boil for 5 minutes.
Drain rice and rinse under cool water in strainer.
Return rice to saucepan and add 1 quart hot milk, lemon zest, cinnamon stick and vanilla.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add sugar.
Stir and simmer for 10 more minutes.
Pour into serving container and let cool.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and serve.

title: homemade salad dressing
directions: Mix together sugar and salt.
Add remaining ingredients, except butter.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Add butter.
When cool, pour mixture over potatoes, hard-boiled eggs, chopped onions and celery.
To be for macaroni or potato salad.

title: no-fat fries
directions: (1)Peel if desired, and cut into fry-size strips. Soak them in several changes of cold water until the water no longer turns cloudy when you swish the pieces around.
This speeds the cooking process.
Drain the potatoes well and spread them on several thicknesses of paper towels as needed.
Remove as much of the surface moisture as possible.
(2) Spread the potatoes on a baking sheet in a single layer.
Sprinkle with black pepper and maybe some herbs of your choosing - cayenne is great for those who like it hot.
(3) Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 20 to 30 minutes. Flip the pieces occasionally so they don't stick to the pan and so that they brown evenly on all sides.
Exact time will depend on the thickness of the potatoes, but what your looking for is a nice, golden color.
Serve with your favorite condiment: ketchup, vinegar, relish or even salsa.

title: croutons
directions: Cut bread into 1/2-inch cubes.
Melt margarine; stir in cheese and seasonings.
Add bread; toss to coat.
Microwave uncovered on High 3 to 5 minutes until lightly browned and sizzling, stirring twice.
Let stand until crisp and cool.
Serve with soup or salad.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Combine ingredients.
Chill 2 hours before serving.

title: bob's german pancakes
directions: Beat egg whites stiff.

title: pepper souffle
directions: Add all ingredients in mixing bowl and stir together.
Pour over Fritos in baking dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: raspberry fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and 1/2 cup jam, beating until smooth.
Add ground cookies and flour; mix well.
Pour batter into a greased 8 x 11-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle chocolate chips evenly over batter. Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
In small saucepan, melt remaining jam over low heat, stirring constantly.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour jam mixture over brownies.
Cool completely in pan.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Store in airtight container.

title: no-bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: In a large saucepan, boil sugar, margarine and milk for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add oatmeal, cocoa, vanilla and peanut butter.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: roach poison
directions: Cut 8-inch squares of pellon and dip in solution of half water and half liquid fabric softener; squeeze out.
Reusable, just dip again.

title: brendan's nana's sausage soup
directions: Break sausage into 1/2-inch pieces.
Put in large soup pot (2-gallon) with sliced onions.
Saute sausage and onion (no oil or butter).
Sausage will release oil when heated.
Saute until golden brown over low heat.
Don't burn the onion.

title: cinnamon buns
directions: Grease Bundt or tube pan.
Sprinkle raisins and chopped nuts on bottom of pan.
Roll each individual frozen roll in cinnamon and place on top of nuts and raisins.
Sprinkle dry vanilla pudding over top.

title: apple cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix ingredients together; add chopped apples.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Combine all but the last ingredient.
Spread mixture on tortillas and roll up tortillas.
Chill, covered, before serving. Cut up rolled tortillas into serving size pieces.

title: microwave apple crisp
directions: Topping:
Mix oats and brown sugar together.
Add butter with fork and make a crumbly mixture.
Set aside.
Combine apples, sugar, flour and cinnamon in 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Stir to mix well.
Sprinkle topping over apple mixture.
Microwave 10 to 12 minutes on High or until apple mixture starts to bubble through topping.

title: rosemary's poppy seed cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Mix well.
Add water and poppy seed.
Pour into tube pan and bake 2 hours in a 325° oven. Cool in pan for 10 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: In bowl, beat eggs; add sugar, oil, vanilla, lemon juice and salt.
Sift together flour, soda and cinnamon.
Add to mixture. Stir in apples and nuts.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Preheat oven to 325° and bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: turkey pot pie
directions: Mix dressing, flour, bouillon and dash of pepper in saucepan. Gradually add milk.
Cook, stirring frequently, over medium-low heat, until thickened.
Add turkey and vegetables.
Cook, stirring until thoroughly heated.
Spoon into 8-inch square baking dish. Unroll dough in 2 rectangles.
Press perforations together to seal.
Cut dough into 1-inch strips and arrange in lattice design over turkey mixture.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.

title: cottage cheese pie
directions: Beat eggs well. Add remaining ingredients. Beat until well blended. Bake in an unbaked crust until set.

title: pat's broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar in small bowl.
Chill and let set for a day.
Combine broccoli, raisins, onions and bacon.
Add dressing.
When you mix the dressing a day ahead, you can mix the salad and set it aside in the refrigerator.
Then blend the dressing in when you are ready to serve.

title: meat balls
directions: Combine hamburger meat, salt, pepper, onion and corn flakes. Mix well.
Form into balls and brown in a skillet.
Place meat balls in a baking dish.
Combine soups and water.
Pour over meat balls.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: potatoes supreme(serves 6)
directions: Cook potatoes in their skins until just tender.
Peel and shred coarsely.
Mix cheese with melted margarine and add potatoes.
Add onions and season with salt and pepper.
Fold in sour cream.
Put in baking dish and sprinkle generously with paprika.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients in order given.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix and nuts.
Sprinkle over mixture in cake dish. Drizzle 1 cup butter over top.
Bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours or until knife comes out clean.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Set aside.
Place Raisin Bran, milk, egg and oil in mixing bowl; beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients to Raisin Bran mixture, stirring only until combined.

title: easy cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a medium bowl and sink cake into it. Then refrigerate overnight.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: almond joy candy
directions: Heat butter and milk until butter melts.
Add coconut.
Cool. Ball this mixture around individual almonds.
Refrigerate until cold.
Dip in melted chocolate.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Mix cake mix and bake as directed in 13x11 pan.
Mix the milk and caramel together.
While cake is hot poke holes in it and pour the caramel mixture over cake.
Let cool completely.
Top with the Cool Whip and sprinkle with candy.
Store in refrigerator.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix flour with soda. Combine in another bowl the margarine, sugars and pudding mix. Beat until smooth and creamy. Beat in eggs.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Drain fat and set aside.
Blend mayonnaise, milk, eggs and cornstarch into skillet.
Stir in meat, cheese, onion, salt and pepper.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes until golden brown or inserted knife comes out clean.

title: golden grahams s'mores
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Heat syrup, butter and chips to boiling, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla. Pour over cereal in bowl; toss until coated.
Fold in marshmallows one cup at a time.
Press in pan with buttered back of spoon.
Let stand 1 hour.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Store, loosely covered, at room temperature up to 2 days.
Makes 24 squares.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add flour alternately with milk; beat well after each addition.
Add vanilla and lemon extracts.
Beat 1 minute at high speed.
Pour into greased and floured tube cake pan.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours. Cool in pan.
Do not invert.

title: mam's easy lasagna
directions: Stir 1 cup of hot water into loaf mix.
Add tomato sauce, tomatoes, oregano, basil and garlic powder.
Grease or spray a 9 x 12-inch or equivalent baking dish.
Cover bottom of dish with a thin layer of sauce mixture.
Arrange 3 noodles on top of sauce. Top with a little sauce and part of cheese mixture.
Repeat process 2 more times, ending with Mozzarella cheese on top.
Top with separated frozen Saucettes.
Cook at 325° for 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: mocha velvet torte
directions: Grease bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan; line with wax paper. Grease wax paper and set aside.
Dissolve coffee granules in boiling water.
Add sugar, stirring until sugar dissolves; set coffee mixture aside.
Position knife blade in food processor bowl; add chocolate morsels.
Process 1 1/2 minutes or until finely chopped, stopping once to scrape down sides.
Pour coffee mixture through food chute with processor running, stopping once to scrape down sides.
Pour butter through food chute with processor running. Add eggs one at a time, through food chute, pulsing after each addition.
Add vanilla and pulse once.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix cookie mix according to recipe on the box and spread onto pizza pan.
Cook until it browns lightly around the edge.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar until creamy.
Spread on cookie crust.
Arrange fruit on pizza cookie as you like.
Mix 1/2 cup pineapple juice and 1/2 cup each juice.
Add 1/4 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cornstarch.
Cook on low heat until dissolved and thick.
Cool and spoon over fruit.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 1-3inch pan.
Fry onion in margarine until tender. Add soup.
Tear tortillas in pieces.
Layer ingredients as follows:
tortillas, soup mixture, chicken, cheese and chilies. Repeat until casserole is full.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Pour off water from grated potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients; beat well.
With a spoon, drop mixture onto hot griddle; spread as thin as possible.
Turn over to fry on other side.
Serve hot with either sour cream or applesauce.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Place meat in a large glass bowl.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Add onion, carrot, celery seed, cloves, peppercorns, wine, vinegar, tarragon and bay leaf to the bowl.
Add enough water so that marinade covers meat.
Marinate meat 4 to 5 days.
Day of serving, remove meat from marinade and reserve. Preheat oven to 300°.
Roast meat 2 1/2 hours.
Sprinkle with the brown sugar, turning meat to coat.
Roast 15 minutes longer. Remove vegetables from the marinade; add the flour to it and pour into the roasting pan.
Add gingersnaps that have been crumbled. Roast meat with gravy 1/2 hour, stirring gravy occasionally.
Let meat rest 10 minutes before slicing.
Serve with gravy and potato pancakes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: vidalia onion rings
directions: Combine flour, salt, egg, milk and oil in a mixing bowl, stirring with a wooden spoon to blend.
Batter may still be slightly lumpy.
Slice onions 1/4-inch thick.
Separate into rings and dip into batter.
Drop into a pot or wok filled with at least 6 inches of cooking oil, heated to 375°.
Cook only until rings are golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix ingredients; pour into baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: helen's lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, flour and salt. Add lemon rind and juice, water and egg yolks.
Cook until thick in double boiler and pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites gradually adding 3 teaspoons sugar and beat until stiff.
Spread on pie. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes to brown.

title: "sloppy joe" casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as package directs; drain.
Meanwhile, prepare seasoning mix with ground beef, tomato paste, tomato sauce and 1 1/4 cups water as package label suggests.
Preheat oven to 350°. In 2 1/2-quart casserole, layer half the macaroni, half the cottage cheese and half the meat sauce; repeat.
Top with Cheddar cheese. Bake uncovered for 40 to 50 minutes or until bubbling.
Serves 6.

title: light-style broccoli soup
directions: Prepare broccoli:
Trim away large woody stalks, then peel outside covering from tender stalks and cut into diagonal slices 1 inch thick.
Divide flowerets into bite-size clumps.
Rinse and set aside to drain.

title: squash casserole
directions: Arrange in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Layer squash, tomato, onion and margarine.
Sprinkle with seasonings.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: southern chicken pie
directions: Stew chicken and remove skin and bones.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken breast with chopped onion until tender. Remove chicken breast from broth, add spaghetti and cook until done. Add cream of chicken soup. cheese rotel and pimento to spaghetti and stir until cheese melts. You may add some water if needed. Place in a baking dish. Cover top with slices of velveeta cheese and sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350 degrees until it bubbles.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir all ingredients together except for raisins.
Beat for one minute.
Add raisins.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: miniature cheesecakes
directions: Cream
ingredients well.
Line tassie pans with papers. Place either
crushed
or
whole	vanilla wafers in bottom of liner. Fill
full with cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 to
20 minutes.
Cool, then top with choice of pie filling (strawberry, cherry, etc.).
Makes 4 1/2 to 5 dozen miniature or 18 large or regular cupcakes.

title: haystacks with frosting
directions: Cream together oleo, brown sugar and egg.
Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix good.
Then add pineapple and nuts.
Drop on greased cookie sheet by teaspoonful.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°. Cut marshmallows in half.
Have them cut and ready as soon as you bring cookies out of oven, put a 1/2 marshmallow on top.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl (defrost potatoes). Pour in a greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: low-fat pork chop casserole
directions: Combine rice, water and cream of mushroom soup.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon of dry onion soup mix over rice mixture.
Trim all visible fat from pork chops.
Arrange on rice mixture.
Sprinkle remaining onion soup mix over pork chops. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 to
1 1/2 hours.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to box.
Pour 1/2 of batter into a floured and greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix apples, flour, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and butter in big bowl with a dash of salt.
After everything is together, on top of pie crust, put sugar and cinnamon.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour or until done at 400° or 425°.

title: artichoke squares
directions: Drain juice from one jar artichokes into a skillet.
Saute onion and garlic in juice.
Drain second jar, discard juice.
Chop all artichokes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Grease 12-cup muffin pan.
Preheat oven to 375°.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Melt cheese, soup and milk in pan over low heat.
Place Doritos in 9 x 14-inch baking dish.
Place chicken on top and pour sauce over and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: pecan crispies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift all dry ingredients and add them to the butter, sugar and egg mixture.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Top each cookie with a whole pecan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350°
from 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: toffee bark
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil.
Heat butter, sugar and water to 300° on candy thermometer.
Pour onto cookie sheet and spread quickly.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and spread when melted.
Top with nuts, if desired.
Put into refrigerator until solid.
Break up and serve.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Cook broccoli per package directions.
Place in 10 x 16-inch baking dish.
Stir together soup and cheese and gradually add milk, mayonnaise and egg to soup mixture.
Stir well until blended.
Pour over broccoli in dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top evenly.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: green vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together the mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice and salt.
Combine vegetables and sauce.
Put in greased casserole dish and cover with crushed Ritz crackers.
Dot with butter and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix flour, soda and salt first, then add remaining ingredients.
Grease and flour pan.
Bake at 325° for an hour and 10 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries, water and sugar until berries pop.
Add cherry Jell-O.
Let almost set, then add celery, apples and nuts. Mix and let set in refrigerator.

title: boy's favorite sugar and spice cookies
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients thoroughly.
Sift the remaining ingredients together and add to first mixture.
Mix well.
Form in balls the size of walnuts.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: blueberry bars
directions: Beat sugar and butter, add eggs, one at a time, beat well, add flour and vanilla.
Dollop teaspoonful of blueberries all across the batter.
Put in jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar while still warm.

title: spanish style shrimp and rice
directions: In a deep 10-inch skillet, heat oil. Add onion, garlic, celery and green pepper. Cook gently, stirring often, until tender but do not brown. Add rice and tomatoes (including the juice), water, salt, pepper, oregano and coriander. Simmer about 20 minutes or until rice is tender and most of liquid is absorbed. Drain shrimp, adding liquid to rice mixture. Add to rice mixture with pimento. Bring to simmer (just to heat shrimp through). Spoon into individual baking dishes (each holding at least 1 1/4 cups). Sprinkle with grated cheese; heat under broiler long enough to melt cheese.

title: "mexican eggs"
directions: Whisk together first 4 ingredients.
Add chilies and cheeses and stir.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Makes 1 quiche.

title: new york cheesecake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, melted butter, 2 tablespoons of sugar and cinnamon in a bowl.
Mix well.
Pat into lightly greased 9-inch spring-form pan.
Beat cream cheese in mixer bowl.
Add 2 cups sugar and eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Fold in sour cream.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Turn off oven.
Let stand in cold oven for 1 hour.
Cool to room temperature.
Remove side of pan.
Chill, covered, in refrigerator for 24 hours before serving.
Yields 16 servings.

title: stuffed green pepper
directions: Cut stem and top from each pepper and remove core and seeds. Saute onion until lightly browned.
Mix together the hamburger, onion, salt, rice and 1/2 can of the soup.
Fill peppers with mixture and place in pan.
Mix remaining soup and water and pour over peppers.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 40 minutes.
Uncover and place bacon on top.
Cook until bacon browns.

title: chocolate fudge delight
directions: Place sugar and milk in heavy pot.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
When mixture boils, lower heat and boil 5 minutes. Place all other ingredients in large bowl.
Pour sugar mixture over chocolate mixture and stir until all chocolate is melted. Add nuts; pour into buttered pans.

title: golden honey-glazed chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Rinse chicken well and pat dry.
Place on a rack in a shallow baking pan.
In a mixing bowl, combine white wine Worcestershire and honey.
Coat chicken with mixture and bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°, basting occasionally, until chicken is golden.
Serves 4.

title: aunt wilma's biscuits
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together, then mix in the next 3 ingredients.
Add the flour and baking powder.
Mix this batter up the day before you need it and let it rise in the refrigerator overnight.
Roll out and cut into biscuits or spread butter, sugar and cinnamon on the top surface and roll it up; cut it with a knife for cinnamon rolls.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Form into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until brown.

title: recipe for a happy heart
directions: Mix together.
Sprinkle with Joy and Understanding.
Bake in the Sunshine and Share with Friends.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt, soda and spices; stir lightly. Cut in shortening.
Stir in molasses and egg.
Shape dough into a ball.
Roll out and cut.
Place on greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Can be rolled in powdered sugar.

title: creamy potatoes
directions: Peel and boil potatoes until tender; drain and mash.
Add sour cream, cream cheese, margarine and chives.
Blend thoroughly with mixer.
Place in a baking dish and garnish as desired with paprika or more chives.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.
May be made ahead of time and not baked until 30 minutes before serving.

title: seasoned popcorn
directions: Stir together butter, garlic powder and oregano.
Pour seasoned butter over popcorn in a large bowl and toss to coat kernels.
Add cheese and toss well.
Serve immediately.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven or large kettle.
Brown chicken, part at a time; remove and keep warm.
Pour off all but 1 tablespoon of oil.
Add onion, garlic and mushrooms; cook 1 minute.
Add tomatoes, sauce, salt and pepper and other seasonings.
Add 1 cup of water or rinse sauce can by filling with water and adding to pot.
Cook for 1 minute.
Return chicken to pot; simmer over low heat for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Add green pepper. Cook several minutes.
Makes 4 servings.
If you want to make 6 servings, increase vegetables.
Great for a main dish.

title: any occasion punch
directions: Mix together all ingredients; fill 2 ice cube trays with punch.
Freeze; use cubes to chill punch.
Decorate punch bowl with sliced oranges.

title: low country boil
directions: Use large pot, 24-quart or bigger.
Fill half full of water. Add shrimp seasoning.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat so water is at a slow boiling stage.
Add potatoes.
cook for 6 minutes.
Add corn; cook 5 minutes.
Add sausage; cook 6 minutes.
Add shrimp; cook 6 minutes or until potatoes and corn are done.
Drain. Serve with shrimp sauce and butter.
Very good.
One dish supper. Serves 4 to 6.

title: ground beef and beans
directions: Cook beef, onion and pepper until brown.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.
Serves 8.

title: zesty tofu salad
directions: Mash tofu with a fork until creamy.
Add all other ingredients.
Season with lemon and salt to taste.
Serve on a garden salad, in a sandwich or as a dip for raw vegetables.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash squash; fold other ingredients and mix.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate eclairs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Heat water and butter to rolling boil in saucepan.
Stir in flour over low heat, stirring vigorously, until mixture forms ball (about 1 minute).
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs thoroughly, one at a time.
Beat until smooth.
Shape with a spatula into 12 fingers, each 4 inches long and 1-inch wide.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes, or until puffed golden brown and dry.
Cool slowly away from drafts.
Cut off tops; scoop out filaments of soft dough.
Fill Eclairs with Custard Filling.
Frost tops with Chocolate Icing.

title: rice krispies crispy fudge
directions: Melt together chocolate, butter and corn syrup over low heat. Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Stir in powdered sugar until smooth.
Add cereal and mix until thoroughly combined.
Spread in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until set.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream together and use star shaped cookie press or make wafers.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 20 to 30 minutes at 300°.

title: dixie dogs
directions: Cook wieners for 5 or 10 minutes in boiling water.
Mix remaining ingredients; dip wieners into batter and deep fry until golden brown.
Serve with mustard.

title: raisin bread
directions: Mix raisins, margarine, soda, boiling water and vanilla.
Let stand 3 to 4 hours or overnight.
When cool, add flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt and eggs.
Butter and flour four coffee cans.
Pour batter 1/2 full.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Wrap in foil as soon as cool.
For muffins, check at 45 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Add all ingredients and mix well.

title: breakfast pie
directions: Brown sausage. Add onion and pepper, until tender, drain. Line pie pan with rolls, add mixture in pan.
Add beaten eggs, and a little milk, season with salt and pepper. Add cheeses. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Place thawed potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch pan or baking dish. Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper.
Mix together the soup, cheese, sour cream and onion.
Pour over potatoes.
Top with crushed corn flakes and drizzle the melted oleo over all.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: cookies(oh, so good!)
directions: Mix and roll out into roll.
Refrigerate 12 hours.
Bake at 300° to 325° until light brown.

title: chocolate-peanut butter cups
directions: Break chocolate bars into small pieces; melt in a double boiler.
Mix 1/2 cup melted peanut butter in with the chocolate. Melt 1 cup peanut butter separately.
Put cupcake liners into a muffin pan.
Put about a tablespoon of chocolate into each cup. Allow this to harden before putting peanut butter next.
Peanut butter needs to harden before placing 1 tablespoon chocolate on top.

title: nut cookies
directions: Mix together softened butter and 12 tablespoons powdered sugar until smooth.
Add flavoring and flour a little at a time.
Add pecans and mix until mixed together.
Chill for 1 hour or more. Roll the dough into the size of your pinkie finger and bake on a well-greased pan or cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes (until lightly browned) at 350°.

title: fruit muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients, add egg and liquids.
Bake in large greased muffin pan for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: jelly cookies
directions: Cream together butter and cream cheese that has been at room temperature.
Gradually add flour.
Chill 2 hours.
Roll and cut into 2-inch squares.
Fill with 1 teaspoon preserves onto each square.
Fold one corner to opposite corner.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.
Cool and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Store in tin cans.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix well the first 7 ingredients.
Pack into loaf pan, leaving space around edge.
Bake at 275° for 3/4 hour.
Drain off fat. Pour pineapple juice over and bake 3/4 hour more at 300°.
Cool before cutting.
Can be removed from pan and reheated to serve.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Mix in other ingredients (except last 2).
Chill until set.
Top with mixture of cream cheese and Cool Whip.

title: easy chocolate pudding milk shake(diabetic; low-fat)
directions: Pour milk into blender container.
Add remaining ingredients. Blend at high speed 15 seconds or until smooth.
Mixture thickens as it stands.
Thin with additional milk if desired.
For a double chocolate impact, use chocolate ice milk instead of vanilla ice milk.
Makes about 5 cups or 5 servings.
(Calories, 150; fat, 2 grams; cholesterol, 10 mg; diabetic exchange per serving:
1/2 2% low-fat milk and 1 starch.)

title: cheese cake
directions: *If you are on a low cholesterol diet use the 6 egg whites instead of the 6 whole eggs and use 1 cup low-fat milk instead of regular milk.

title: best pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and butter. Add sugar and cream until smooth. Add eggs, one at a time while mixing. Sift baking powder into flour and add to mixture alternately with milk. When mixture is well blended, add vanilla and lemon extract. Mix well. Bake at 350° in a tube pan 1 hour and 20 minutes. Do not open oven door during baking time.

title: white trash *
directions: You will need 1 white unscented kitchen trash bag.

title: six baked apples
directions: Wash apples.
Pare a strip from the top of each apple.
Core apple.
Fill apple with raisins, chopped dates or pecans.
Place on a baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and bring to a boil. Pour syrup over apples and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, eggs, meal, salt and vanilla together.
Put pecans in bottom of unbaked pie shell.
Pour mixture over nuts. Add butter to top of pie.
Bake in low oven for 30 minutes.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Prepare popcorn first.
Must have a large bowl.
In a 2-quart saucepan, melt the margarine along with brown sugar, Karo and salt.
Bring to a boil and then boil for 5 minutes, stirring periodically.
Remove from heat.
Add baking soda and stir in quickly and thoroughly.
(Mixture will raise in saucepan.) Immediately pour over popcorn and mix well.
Spread in two cookie sheets.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes to coat evenly.
Cool and store in airtight container.

title: cooked german chocolate frosting
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add evaporated milk, then sugar and margarine.
Mix well.
Cook 12 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Add coconut, chopped nuts and vanilla.
Mix, then spread on German Chocolate or Marble Fudge Cake while frosting is warm.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Brush thinly sliced bread (crusts removed) with melted butter. Press into muffin tin.
Toast in moderate oven (350°).
Fill with tuna, hamburg, chicken, deviled ham or any desired filling.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onion.
Add chicken and 1/2 of green chilies.
Pour 1/3 of soup mixture into chicken.
Add 1/2 green chilies.
Roll into corn tortillas.
Pour remaining soup mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
The last 15 minutes, top with cheese and finish baking.

title: macadamia cream pie
directions: Unwrap cream cheese and put it into a 2-quart casserole. Microwave on 50% (Medium) 1 to 1 1/2 minutes. Blend in peanut butter, then milk.
Stir in sugar.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Line rhubarb in pan.
Sprinkle jello over rhubarb.
Pour marshmallows over it and sprinkle sugar over it.

title: holiday punch
directions: Mix Jell-O and Kool-Aid by directions and add to remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2 Tupperware containers.
To serve, put 1 frozen portion in punch bowl.
Allow to stand and thaw a bit. Break apart and use 1/2 of the 7-Up.
Add remaining portions as necessary.
Serves 30.

title: zucchini-tomato skillet(yields 6 servings)
directions: In a large skillet, saute onion.
Add mushrooms and zucchini for 5 minutes, stirring often.
Add tomato slices.
Cook 3 or 4 minutes, stirring through gently.
Drain off juice that has formed. Then stir in parsley, Parmesan cheese, basil, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Stir and cook over medium heat just until heated through.
Sprinkle with the Cheddar cheese.
Cover for 3 to 5 minutes until cheese is melted.
Or transfer to shallow serving dish, sprinkle cheese over and pop under broiler until cheese melts.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: In a saucepan, place zucchini and cover with water.
Add lemon juice and bring to boil.
Once boiling, reduce heat and simmer a minute or two.
Remove from heat and drain well.
Butter a 10-inch pie pan and combine zucchini with ham, nuts, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
In a blender, combine whipping cream, eggs and Parmesan cheese, mixing thoroughly.
Pour cream mixture over zucchini and ham and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine in sauce pan.
Place on medium heat until it starts to boil;
boil for 1 minute and remove from heat.
Add vanilla, salt, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Stir well.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Cool.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit in quarters.
Shake biscuits in bag with sugar and cinnamon.
Layer biscuits in Bundt cake pan (greased and floured).
Sprinkle nuts on bottom of pan and between layers, if desired.
Make layers until biscuits are all used.
Melt brown sugar and butter together and boil for 1 minute.
Pour over biscuits and bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes and invert on plate.
To serve, just pinch off and eat with fingers. Monkey see, monkey do!

title: holiday gravy
directions: Blend in a bowl 1 cup cold broth with flour until smooth. Heat remaining broth with bouillon cubes in saucepan.
Stir flour mixture into hot broth.
Cook and stir over moderate heat until mixture thickens.
Reduce heat.
Add Kitchen Bouquet and pepper. Makes about 4 cups.
Contains 1% fat, less than 1 gram per serving.

title: stuffed deer heart
directions: Cut pocket in heart.
Remove extra fat and string from around top of heart.
Soak in cold, salt water for 15 minutes.
Wipe dry. Stuff heart with chopped onion and dressing using toothpicks, skewers or string to fasten opening.
Brown all sides of stuffed heart.
Add whole onion, salt and pepper.
Add water to Dutch oven and cook for 3 to 4 hours.
Slice heart thinly after removing dressing.

title: mandarin chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, lemon juice, onion and salt. Stir well. Cover and chill. Add mayonnaise, sliced grapes, oranges and almonds to chicken mixture. Toss well. Serve on lettuce arranged on platter. Garnish with oranges and grapes. Makes 6 servings.

title: russian teacakes
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla; mix in sifted flour and salt. Add nuts.
Roll into balls.
Cook 10-12 minutes at 400°.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm; cool and roll in sugar again.

title: old-fashioned rice pudding
directions: Mix rice well with other ingredients.
Bake 20 minutes in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish (Pyrex) at 350°.

title: no bake chocolate pie crust
directions: Mix ingredients and press on bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie pan and chill until ready to fill.

title: mexican baked chicken
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Set aside.
In a shallow bowl, beat together eggs, garlic and 1/4 cup salsa.
In another bowl, combine bread crumbs, chili powder, cumin and oregano.
Dip each chicken piece in egg mixture. Drain briefly.
Then coat with crumb mixture and shake off excess.

title: persimmon ice cream(parke county indiana covered bridge festival)
directions: Mix ingredients in electric mixer until thick and creamy.
Put in ice cream freezer and finish filling with milk to within 3 1/2 to 4 inches of top; freeze.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: In skillet,
saute onion in oil until tender.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, cumin, chili powder, salsa, salt and pepper. Simmer, stirring occasionally, for 20 to 25 minutes.
In the middle of each tortilla, place a few teaspoons of each cheese and a few pieces of chicken; moisten the edge with sauce.
Roll up tortillas and place in a baking dish. Pour sauce over the enchiladas and sprinkle on remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until tortillas are lightly browned and cheese has melted.
Serve with sour cream.

title: hot crab fondue
directions: In top of a double boiler, combine cheese and cream cheese. Stir until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients; stir until blended.
If fondue thickens on standing, add a little cream.

title: fluffy banana cake
directions: Sift the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Beat the shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add the buttermilk or sour milk.
Add alternately the mashed bananas and flour mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chinese walnut chicken
directions: Skin and bone chicken; cut into 1-inch pieces.
Heat oil; saute walnuts 2 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Add chicken and stir-fry 2 minutes.
Add ham and walnuts; stir-fry 5 minutes. Stir in soy sauce, salt, pepper, sugar and chicken broth; cook 2 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with 1 tablespoon of water and stir into mixture to slightly thicken.
Serve over cooked rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute squash
in
water
with
onion.
Cook until done. Fry bacon.
Drain
excess water off squash.
Mix with crumbled bacon. Place in casserole dish and top with cheese.
Let melt in 350° oven.
Stir.
Cook for additional 20 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix flour, milk and sugar and pour into casserole in which 1 stick of margarine has been melted.
Pour in fruit.
Bake until brown in 400° oven.

title: reese's cup dessert
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients real well.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread frosting on top.
Chill and slice.

title: moist and creamy coconut cake
directions: Bake 1 package white or yellow cake mix in 9 x 13-inch pan as per package directions.
Cool 15 minutes; poke holes with a utility fork.
Bring to boil and simmer 1 minute, 1 1/2 c. milk, 1/2 c. sugar and 1/2 cup coconut.
Spoon mixture over cake, cool, fold 1/2 c. coconut into 1 (8 oz.) cool whip and spread on cake.
Sprinkle coconut on top.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: taco pie
directions: Cook ground beef and onion until browned; drain.
Stir in seasoning.
Spread on greased pie plate.
Beat milk, eggs and Bisquick until smooth.
Pour on meat mixture on pie plate.
Bake for 25 minutes in a 400° oven.
Top with tomato slices and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake about 10 minutes longer or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Cool about 5 minutes.
Serve topped with sour cream, chopped tomatoes and shredded lettuce.
Serves 6.

title: date dainties
directions: Separate eggs; beat yolks.
Add sugar, then cream together. Add flour, baking powder, nuts and dates; mix well.
Fold into stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in waxed paper lined pan in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: fluffy fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1 cup juice in saucepan.
To saucepan, add sugar, flour, eggs, orange and lemon juice and oil. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and let cool.
In a salad bowl, combine pineapple, fruit cocktail, oranges and bananas.
Fold in whipped cream and cooked sauce.
Chill several hours.
Makes 12-16 servings.

title: fat-free pineapple banana bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
In another bowl, combine egg whites, banana, pineapple, sugar and milk.
Beat well.
Stir into dry ingredients.
Pour into medium loaf pan (8 1/2 x 5-inch) sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool for slicing.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender; drain.
Mix remaining ingredients. Put into casserole and bake 45 minutes at 400°.

title: peanut butter cup brownies
directions: You will need cupcake papers and cupcake tins.

title: pork bake
directions: Brown pork steaks in frying pan.
Make stuffing with remaining ingredients.
Put one pork steak on bottom. Add stuffing mixture and top with second pork steak.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours.

title: buttermilk sheet cake
directions: Separate eggs and beat egg whites.
Add 3/4 cup sugar and refrigerate.
Cream 1 cup butter and Crisco.
Stir in 2 1/4 cups of sugar; add buttermilk and soda.
Add flour, salt and extract. Bake 20 minutes at 375° for sheet cake.

title: fruit freeze
directions: Soak the gelatin in 1/4 cup water for 5 minutes.
Pour into the hot apple juice and stir until dissolved.
Add sugar and stir over low heat until the sugar is dissolved.
Cool.
Add lemon or orange juice, pineapple juice, water and ginger ale.
Pour into freezer trays and freeze to a mush.
Remove and beat with a hand or electric beater.
Freeze again to a mush.
Serve with long spoons.
Makes about 2 quarts.

title: worlds best corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well. Pour into a greased 9 inch pan and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Bring all tomato sauces combined to a boil.
Lower heat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 4 to 5 hours.
Makes approximately 17 to 18 quarts.
Season to taste

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together the sour cream, cream cheese and taco seasoning for the bottom layer.
Layer the lettuce, diced tomatoes, diced onions and shredded cheese on top.
Refrigerate and serve with tortilla chips.

title: arabian squash casserole
directions: Peel and grate squash.
Mix with the salt and let stand 20 minutes.
Press all liquid from squash.
Mix together squash, cheese and cottage cheese, eggs, bread crumbs, parsley and pepper. Put in a buttered 3-quart casserole.
Pour butter on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: fudge cake
directions: Cream shortening with brown sugar and add cocoa.
Add eggs and beat well.
Alternately add 1/2 cup buttermilk and 2 cups flour, beating until smooth.
Add 1/2 cup boiling water and blend.
Stir in vanilla and salt.
Add soda last.
Pour into two 9-inch pans and bake at 350° to 375° for 25 minutes.
Cover with powdered sugar icing.

title: 2 coconut pies
directions: Combine and cook until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add the coconut.
Have 2 pie shells baked.
Fill with filling.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar to egg whites.
Top pies; sprinkle with coconut.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Crush potato chips.
Flake tuna into bite-size; add soup and vegetables.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake 10 to 25 minutes.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend well.
Add meat, cover and marinate 3 hours or overnight.
Turn occasionally.

title: green beans with a flair(glamorize with cashews)
directions: Cut ends off beans.
Cut beans into 2-inch pieces and place in a large saucepan with boiling, salted water.
Cover; cook until tender, but still crisp, 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain and rinse under cold water to stop the cooking process.
May be refrigerated overnight.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions. Chill. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Refrigerate several hours or overnight before serving.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook
noodles and butter.
Put	in
x
13-inch
pan. Layer sauerkraut, then
corned
beef;
mix rest of ingredients together except cheese and layer over meat, then layer cheese. Bake in 350° oven,
covered.
Bake
last 10 minutes uncovered. Should be 35 minutes total.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes in water as if you were going to make mashed potatoes.
Drain potatoes and set aside.
Melt butter and saute onions.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper, if desired.
Stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat until mixture is bubbly and slightly thickened.
Add cooked potatoes.
You may also add cooked country ham cut into small pieces or top with cooled crumbled bacon.
Heat slightly longer or add cheese until melted.

title: taco salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together.
Just before serving, add taco chips and a large bottle of Catalina salad dressing.
If not served immediately, wait to add taco chips and dressing so that chips do not get soggy.

title: meat balls
directions: Combine all ingredients, except barbecue sauce and mushrooms. Form in medium size balls.
Put balls in pan and pour barbecue sauce over balls.
Let bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Take out of oven, add 1 can mushrooms and package of cocktail wieners.
Let bake for 5 more minutes.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Combine and cook to bubble; then pour over 10 to 12 cups of popped popcorn.
Stir until all is coated, then form into balls.

title: red devil dip
directions: Combine all ingredients for a delicious dip.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Blend first 2 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and pour into unbaked shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican succotash
directions: In large skillet that has a cover.
Saute onion in margarine until soft.

title: carrot and pineapple bread
directions: Combine ingredients in order given.
Mix well.	Pour in two greased loaf pans.	Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: zesty lo-cal french
directions: Combine cornstarch and water in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until smooth and clear.
Put all remaining ingredients in blender and blend to 3 to 4 minutes. Stir into cornstarch mix and cook until smooth.
Remove from heat. Cool.
Store in refrigerator.
Keeps well. Makes about 1 quart.

title: spinach brownies
